l which is in keeping with the volume. There are few red wines in the world like this. It\'s fully dry, with potent flavors of baked blackberries, blackcurrants, cola and peppery spices, and the tannins are huge, but negotiable. Demands the richest grilled meats and cheeses.','US','California','Rockpile','Sonoma','Mauritson','Rockpile Cemetary Vineyard'),(124,49,12,92,40.00,'Henry\'s Drive Vignerons 2006 Parson\'s Flat Shiraz-Cabernet Sauvignon (Padthaway)','The blend is roughly two-thirds Shiraz and one-third Cabernet, and the result combines berries with cassis and generosity with structure, all framed by toasty oak. Savory in character, long and dusty on the finish. Drink now-2018.','Australia','South Australia','Padthaway',NULL,'Henry\'s Drive Vignerons','Parson\'s Flat'),(125,9,9,92,45.00,'Silverado 2006 Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','This sophisticated wine is mostly Cabernet Sauvignon, which accounts for the firm tannins and dense structure as well as most of the blackberries and blackcurrants. Smaller amounts of Merlot and Cabernet Franc add cherries and violets, while oak contributes smoky complexities. Rich and elegant, the wine provides lovely drinking now.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Silverado',NULL),(126,9,2,91,45.00,'Le Riche 2003 Cabernet Sauvignon Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon (Stellenbosch)','Etienne Le Riche is a total Cabernet specialist. With a tiny production of 5,000 cases across all his wines, this is boutique in the best sense. The Reserve Cabernets are, of course, the stars. This 2003 is fruit and wood driven, a powerful but still elegant wine, with black plums, tannins and super-ripe fruits.','South Africa','Stellenbosch',NULL,NULL,'Le Riche','Cabernet Sauvignon Reserve'),(127,8,9,91,48.00,'Pierre Sparr 2007 Vendages Tardives Gewurztraminer (Alsace)','Mid-gold color. Pronounced and enticing aromas of ripe citrus and stone fruit, layered with honey and floral notes with a touch of sweet spice. Rich and creamy texture packed with sweet ripe juicy fruit, honey, spice and a twist of sage. Off-dry, deliciously smooth with fresh acidity and medium-body. An elegant wine with a long, creamy, spicy finish.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Pierre Sparr','Vendages Tardives'),(128,1,9,91,13.00,'Pierre Sparr 2008 Alsace One White (Alsace)','Attractive mid-gold color with intense aromas of ripe citrus and stone fruit, strong minerality and hints of spice. Racy with crisp acidity, juicy, rich and smooth texture with lots of concentrated, bright flavors of blood orange, peach, apricot, mango and spice. Strong minerality follows through to a long, precise, juicy finish.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Pierre Sparr','Alsace One'),(129,50,9,91,17.00,'Kuentz-Bas 2008 Pinot Blanc (Alsace)','Compelling minerality on the nose, Refined and focused floral aromas with ample ripe stone fruit and a hint of petrol. Racy acidity and lovely taut palate with generous layers of juicy ripe peach, apricot and nectarine.  Strong minerality prevails across the palate leading to a lingering finish. Very balanced.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Kuentz-Bas',NULL),(130,32,9,91,25.00,'Camberley 2004 Philosophers\' Stone Red (Stellenbosch)','A big, black bruiser of a wine that has black olive flavors and aromas and plenty beyond. Raspberry, mulberry, vanilla and spice all vie on the nose, while the palate is so dark it´s tough to discern the plum and leather flavors. Give it three years and reap the benefits.','South Africa','Stellenbosch',NULL,NULL,'Camberley','Philosophers\' Stone'),(131,48,9,91,70.00,'Ceretto 2003 Bricco Rocche Brunate  (Barolo)','At the first it was quite muted and subdued, but over a ten minute period it developed beautifully in the glass. The dark fruit is still dominant, but it is beginning to show some interesting tertiary aromas of earth, mushrooms and leather. Well balanced with a medium finish. Needs a few more years, but can be enjoyed now with a good deal of pleasure.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Ceretto','Bricco Rocche Brunate'),(132,51,9,91,20.00,'Dopff & Irion 2008 Gentil White (Alsace)','Attractive mid-gold color. Compelling layers of tangy citrus and stone fruit aromas with notes of honey and earthy minerality. Intense flavors of honey, tangy orange citrus, sweet peach and apricot that are both rich and juicy.  Crisp acidity provides a perfect balance for the slight sweetness on the finish. Taut and focused.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Dopff & Irion','Gentil'),(133,9,2,91,30.00,'Delheim 2001 Grand Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon (Simonsberg-Stellenbosch)','A Cabernet-dominated (98%) wine, which boasts a dense, concentrated tannic structure. Flavors of cassis underly this, while the wood spices contribute their ribbon of flavor. This is an impressive wine, the flagship red from this estate founded by Spatz Sperling over 30 years ago.','South Africa','Simonsberg-Stellenbosch',NULL,NULL,'Delheim','Grand Reserve'),(134,48,9,91,68.00,'Poderi Luigi Einaudi 2003  Barolo','Einaudi\'s wines have been improving lately, and this Barolo was very impressive, given the trying conditions of the vintage. Big rich, fat with smoked meat and a good dose of oak, the wine was one of the few that didn\'t peter out early but stayed on the palate to the end, culminating in an nice easy finish.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Poderi Luigi Einaudi',NULL),(135,9,9,91,78.00,'Clark-Clauden 2007 Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','Give this young Cab time in the cellar to come around. Right now, it\'s fresh and tannic, with primary fruit blackberry and cherry flavors, and the sweet smoky oak hasn\'t been integrated. Should knit together over the next 4-6 years, at least.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Clark-Clauden',NULL),(136,48,9,91,60.00,'Giacomo Ascheri 2001 Sorano  (Barolo)','The color is just beginning to show signs of browning at the edge, but the wine is still fresh and vibrant. The nose is complex, showing licorice, summer fruits, caramel and roses. On the palate, it is soft and pleasant, but lacks some concentration.  At its peak, but will drink well for a few years.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Giacomo Ascheri','Sorano'),(137,32,12,91,50.00,'Lassègue 2003  Saint-Émilion','This wine\'s black cherry and plum flavors veer dangerously toward prune—no doubt a product of the exceedingly hot summer. It\'s creamy and supple in texture, adding just enough tobacco, vanilla and smoke for complexity. But for all the fruit and ripeness, it finishes with great elegance and precision. Drink now–2020. Imported by Acadia Imports.','France','Bordeaux','Saint-Émilion',NULL,'Lassègue',NULL),(138,18,2,90,NULL,'Beaumont 2005 Hope Marguerite Chenin Blanc (Walker Bay)','This is great Chenin Blanc, wood fermented but still leaving all the varietal character. Rich, creamy, almond flavors and silky smooth, which keeps all the essential acidity of the grape, with added spice and vanilla.','South Africa','Walker Bay',NULL,NULL,'Beaumont','Hope Marguerite'),(139,51,9,90,10.00,'Dopff & Irion 2008 Crustacés White (Alsace)','Mid-gold color. Very mineral driven with subtle aromas of bruised apple and stone fruit compote. Crisp, fairly taut palate showing strong minerality and ripe flavors of red apple, cantaloupe, sweet nectarine and spice. Taut and precise texture with a long, slightly austere finish.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Dopff & Irion','Crustacés'),(140,3,9,90,112.00,'Kuentz-Bas 2007 Cuvée Jerémy Sélection de Grains Nobles Pinot Gris (Alsace)','Beautiful deep gold color. Intense, concentrated nose with vibrant aromas of honey, citrus marmalade and savory botrytis notes. Deliciously sweet and succulent, yet balanced by good acidity.  Packed with flavors of sweet ultra-ripe stone and tropical fruit, with honey and botrytis notes following through. Strong minerality prevails to a long, complex finish.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Kuentz-Bas','Cuvée Jerémy Sélection de Grains Nobles'),(141,52,9,90,26.00,'Poderi Colla 2005 Costa Bruna  (Barbera d\'Alba)','A big, fat, luscious wine with plenty of toasty oak, dark jammy fruit and spices. The palate showed the same lushness; with the fruit front and center with surprising length.  A delicious, rather hefty effort short on finesse but long on flavor.','Italy','Piedmont','Barbera d\'Alba',NULL,'Poderi Colla','Costa Bruna'),(142,48,9,90,45.00,'Giacomo Ascheri 2003 Vigna dei Pola  (Barolo)','This is one of the more complex wines from the 2003 vintage. The nose has aromas of blackberry liquer, smoked meat, truffle and road tar. On the palate the fruit seems a little heavier and more roasted, but still melds well with its earthy, mushroomy flavors. Medium finish.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Giacomo Ascheri','Vigna dei Pola'),(143,4,9,90,17.00,'Banyan 2007 Riesling (Santa Lucia Highlands)','A beautiful wine, sleek, crisp and ultra-dry, with the most refined flavors of petrol, white peach, kaffir lime, apricot skin and minerals. The acidity is very high and palate-cleansing. The wine was half fermented in barrels, half in stainless steel. Sommeliers, buy this by the case, if you can find it.','US','California','Santa Lucia Highlands','Central Coast','Banyan',NULL),(144,3,9,90,84.00,'Domaine Zind-Humbrecht 2007 Hunawihr Clos Windsbuhl Pinot Gris (Alsace)','Rich gold in color. Broad, layered aromas of very ripe fruit with hints of sweet smoke, brown sugar, honey and a savory earthy minerality. Full-bodied, bone dry, but richly textured with crisp acidity and a wide palette of flavors, ripe stone fruit, a creamy savory earthiness, sage and a balsamic kick on the finish. Very long length, slightly warm but with a lingering savory, mineral finish.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Domaine Zind-Humbrecht','Hunawihr Clos Windsbuhl'),(145,9,7,91,85.00,'Terra Valentine 2013 K Block Cabernet Sauvignon (Spring Mountain District)','Thick and brooding, this dark, sweetly tannic wine also offers higher-toned elements of cedar, dried herb and graphite. It finds its balance amid a full-bodied density of fruit concentration and girth of structure. Drink now through 2023.','US','California','Spring Mountain District','Napa','Terra Valentine','K Block'),(146,5,8,91,64.00,'Testarossa 2013 Guidotti Vineyard Pinot Noir (Santa Lucia Highlands)','Cooked cranberry is spiced with anise, peppercorn and roasted beef slices on this bottling from a vineyard planted by three brothers who are longtime Salinas Valley farmers. The palate shows dark cranberry and raspberry, spiced up by chopped sage, thyme and bay leaf.','US','California','Santa Lucia Highlands','Central Coast','Testarossa','Guidotti Vineyard'),(147,9,8,91,68.00,'Vincent Vineyards 2010 Family Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon (Santa Ynez Valley)','There\'s a touch of hot asphalt, pencil lead and miso on the nose of this first vintage from a promising, well-funded project, with dark elderberry fruit and dried dill rounding out the aromas. The palate blends a gamy beef quality with oregano, marjoram, cooked strawberry, baked blackberry and a sesame-oil character.','US','California','Santa Ynez Valley','Central Coast','Vincent Vineyards','Family Reserve'),(148,9,8,91,68.00,'Vincent Vineyards 2012 Family Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon (Santa Ynez Valley)','Black cherry, black plum and black currant are integrated well into the fresh dill and smoke scents on the nose of this wine from one of the region\'s newest properties. It discloses a rich dark-chocolate sauce character on the palate as well as black-currant-jelly flavors, but most impressive is the lush, sexy and soft mouthfeel.','US','California','Santa Ynez Valley','Central Coast','Vincent Vineyards','Family Reserve'),(149,4,6,91,16.00,'Weingut Liebfrauenstift 2014 Dry Riesling (Rheinhessen)','Crisp, pristine peach and apricot notes resonate through the nose and palate of this fresh, blossomy dry Riesling. While zesty and lithe in body, ripe grapefruit and melon flavors feel supple and silky on the palate. Drink now through 2019.','Germany','Rheinhessen',NULL,NULL,'Weingut Liebfrauenstift','Dry'),(150,53,8,91,35.00,'Wrath 2013 Destruction Level Red (Monterey)','Smashed blackberry and blueberry fruit are enhanced by burned caramel, heavy slate and touches of soy and smoke on the nose. There\'s great depth in both body and flavors once sipped, with a layer of fine-grained tannins revealing teriyaki, black plum, boysenberry and touches of lavender.','US','California','Monterey','Central Coast','Wrath','Destruction Level'),(151,9,7,91,25.00,'Yardstick 2013 Ruth\'s Reach Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','This wine shows off Yountville fruit at its finest, starting with a floral component to the nose. Spicy, bright and lifted, it coats the palate in ripe berry and cherry, ending with a snap of vanilla.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Yardstick','Ruth\'s Reach'),(152,54,2,91,30.00,'Herdade Grande 2014 Gerações Colheita Seleccionada Branco White (Alentejano)','This bottling shows a rich, wood-aged wine, full of ripe yellow and tropical fruits as well as rich toasty flavors. The wine is warm, rounded, spicy and with its impressive structure still developing, it has the potential to age well. The wine is named to celebrate the second Lança generation in charge at the estate. Drink from 2017.','Portugal','Alentejano',NULL,NULL,'Herdade Grande','Gerações Colheita Seleccionada Branco'),(153,5,8,91,55.00,'Albatross Ridge 2012 Estate Reserve Pinot Noir (Carmel Valley)','From a promising new project, the nose of this wine is linear and focused, with black raspberry, black licorice, cola, wet sagebrush and rain-on-slate scents. The tactile acidity once sipped creates a fascinating soft buzz on the tongue, with flavors of dried mint, brisk raspberry and cherry tomato. Camphor and eucalyptus add intrigue on the finish.','US','California','Carmel Valley','Central Coast','Albatross Ridge','Estate Reserve'),(154,47,8,91,46.00,'Alta Colina 2012 Old 900 Syrah (Paso Robles)','Dark and thick in the glass, this wine shows strong but not bitter tar notes on the nose plus charred beef in a blueberry glaze, wet campfire, bourbon barrel and vanilla. The structure is massive now, gooey with thick tannins and flavors of espresso bean and condensed purple flowers. Judicious acidity ensures strong cellaring potential. Drink 2018–2027.','US','California','Paso Robles','Central Coast','Alta Colina','Old 900'),(155,55,5,91,50.00,'Marques de Griñon 2010 Single Vineyard Estate Bottled Graciano (Dominio de Valdepusa)','Ripe aromas of raisin, black plum and horsehide are pointy and peppery. On the palate, this Graciano is bold and energetic, with lifting acidity. Loud berry flavors come with strong accents of dark chocolate and bitter espresso, while the finish is long but just moderate in complexity. Drink through 2020.','Spain','Central Spain','Dominio de Valdepusa',NULL,'Marques de Griñon','Single Vineyard Estate Bottled'),(156,47,8,91,36.00,'Big Basin 2013 Syrah (Santa Cruz Mountains)','Bradley Brown\'s appellation blend is a nice entry point to this exciting winery. This wine shows lavish smoked black currant and plum flavors, with aromatically lifting spices of anise and black pepper and a savory roast-beef element. The palate packs lots of pepper and relies on plump black cherry, boysenberry and a dark-chocolate syrup richness.','US','California','Santa Cruz Mountains','Central Coast','Big Basin',NULL),(157,4,6,91,14.00,'Carl Graff 2014 Graacher Himmelreich Spätlese Riesling (Mosel)','Approachably fruity yet nuanced and electrifying, there\'s exceptional value here. High-intensity flavors of tangerine and stone fruit sweeten the palate, balanced by nerve-tingling acidity and deep ripples of slate, salt and honeycomb. It\'s an intensely zesty wine, but the finish has length and power.','Germany','Mosel',NULL,NULL,'Carl Graff','Graacher Himmelreich Spätlese'),(158,2,2,91,26.00,'Casa Santa Vitória 2013 Grande Reserva Tinto Red (Alentejano)','From an estate in the south of the Alentejo, this is a rich, hot-country wine. It is firm, densely structured and with solid, dark tannins. There is a juicy black fruit background to this dense wine that gives a lift. Still young, this dark and very concentrated wine will be better from 2018.','Portugal','Alentejano',NULL,NULL,'Casa Santa Vitória','Grande Reserva Tinto'),(159,29,1,91,38.00,'Castello di Gabbiano 2012 Bellezza Gran Selezione  (Chianti Classico)','Baked plum, Asian spice, vanilla and menthol aromas carry the nose. The elegantly structured palate offers fleshy black cherry, licorice, mint and well-integrated French oak alongside fine-grained tannins that lend firm, polished support. A coffee note marks the finish.','Italy','Tuscany','Chianti Classico',NULL,'Castello di Gabbiano','Bellezza Gran Selezione'),(160,29,1,91,NULL,'Castello Romitorio 2011 Filo di Seta  (Brunello di Montalcino)','Intense aromas of ripe red berry, menthol, espresso and star anise lead the nose. The concentrated palate offers cranberry, dried Morello cherry, sage and licorice alongside close-grained tannins that grip the finish. Drink from 2018 through 2025.','Italy','Tuscany','Brunello di Montalcino',NULL,'Castello Romitorio','Filo di Seta'),(161,12,2,91,35.00,'Château Vincens 2012 Malbec (Cahors)','Low-yield vines on the best parcels of the Vincens estate are the source of this wine. It is super-rich and concentrated, maybe too much in its opulent excess. The wine does have great plum and berry flavors that are generous and full in the mouth. The wine even now is still young and will be better from 2018.','France','Southwest France','Cahors',NULL,'Château Vincens',NULL),(162,15,8,91,35.00,'Chronic Cellars 2013 Mr. Nibbles Red (Paso Robles)','A hearty blend of 76% Zinfandel and 24% Petite Sirah, this bottling packs a wallop of cinnamon-stick on the nose as well as strawberry puree, licorice and black pepper. Clove, allspice, and nutmeg arise immediately on the sip, backed by baked plum and bay leaf notes.','US','California','Paso Robles','Central Coast','Chronic Cellars','Mr. Nibbles'),(163,4,8,91,28.00,'Claiborne & Churchill 2014 Claiborne Vineyard Riesling (Edna Valley)','More complex than the winery\'s appellation blend, yet also requiring time to reach full potential, this shows delicate lemon slices, honeysuckle, surf wax, pink grapefruit and a touch of coconut on the nose. The palate is grippy in texture and sizzling with mouthwatering acidity, offering lemon rind, grapefruit spritz and petrol flavors. Expect inviting nut and honey-dust flavors to emerge. Drink 2018–2034.','US','California','Edna Valley','Central Coast','Claiborne & Churchill','Claiborne Vineyard'),(164,19,2,91,NULL,'Collin-Bourisset 2011 Hospices Civils de Romanèche Thurins  (Moulin-à-Vent)','Produced from vineyards donated to a charitable hospital in the 19th century, this wine is rich and now perfectly mature. It has smoky tannins that lie under the fine, elegant cherry and red plum fruits and acidity. The wine still has freshness although the attraction here is the ripe structure. The ornate label dates back to 1926.','France','Beaujolais','Moulin-à-Vent',NULL,'Collin-Bourisset','Hospices Civils de Romanèche Thurins'),(165,15,5,91,29.00,'Conde de Velázquez 2012 Condesa Real Premium Blend Red (Aconcagua Valley)','This blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Syrah and Merlot opens with blackened aromas of charred oak and creosote, but it quickly sheds that oak-heavy character to display toasty flavors of olives, herbs and berry fruits. All together, this is a classic Chilean red blend, with fine tannins and patented lightly herbal, balsamic flavors. Drink through 2020.','Chile','Aconcagua Valley',NULL,NULL,'Conde de Velázquez','Condesa Real Premium Blend'),(166,9,5,91,32.00,'Cono Sur 2012 20 Barrels Cabernet Sauvignon (Maipo Valley)','Dry, briary aromas of field brush, black olive, herbs, berry fruits and saucy tomato are textbook Maipo. This is fresh, a touch choppy, and not overly heavy. Flavors of cassis, plum and vanilla carry over to the finish, which is fresh and bolstered by fine natural acidity. Drink through 2022.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'Cono Sur','20 Barrels'),(167,56,2,91,25.00,'Domaine Berthoumieu 2013 Charles de Batz Tannat-Cabernet (Madiran)','Of course, this 90% Tannat wine is still very young. But it\'s impressive, rich and concentrated and promises to age well. It is dense with both tannins and fruit, black plum and berry flavors dominating, cut by acidity. It will be ready to drink from 2019.','France','Southwest France','Madiran',NULL,'Domaine Berthoumieu','Charles de Batz'),(168,30,8,91,28.00,'Dracaena 2013 Cabernet Franc (Paso Robles)','The addition of 15% Petite Sirah takes this bottling to a compelling place, showing barely ripe blackberries, animal fat, smoke, black pepper and a wild clove element on the nose. It\'s rich and layered on the palate, where chalky tannins support black cherry, grilled beef and mint flavors. This has the bones to last awhile.','US','California','Paso Robles','Central Coast','Dracaena',NULL),(169,16,7,91,95.00,'Duckhorn 2012 Rector Creek Vineyard Merlot (Napa Valley)','A fairly elegant expression of the variety, this wine is bright in cherry kirsch and pretty aromas of rose petal and lavender, structured to age and enjoy with food. Rector Creek Vineyard is just north of Yountville and planted in rocky alluvial soils. Drink now through 2022.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Duckhorn','Rector Creek Vineyard'),(170,5,7,91,44.00,'Dutton-Goldfield 2014 Dutton Ranch Pinot Noir (Russian River Valley)','This wine is put together from multiple vineyard sources, including the well-known Morelli Lane and Widdoes, all farmed by the Duttons. Larger in production than many of the vineyard-designates, it offers baked bread and juicy overtones of cranberry-raspberry layered atop luxuriously toasted oak. It\'ll show well at the table.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Dutton-Goldfield','Dutton Ranch'),(171,4,6,91,30.00,'Fritz Haag 2014 Brauneberger Feinherb Riesling (Mosel)','Fresh and fragrant of blossoms, tart yellow peach and apricot, this off-dry Riesling maintains a crystalline fruit purity that persists throughout Fritz Haag\'s wines. It\'s invigorating and irresistably quaffable. The long, melon-rind finish is lip smacking.','Germany','Mosel',NULL,NULL,'Fritz Haag','Brauneberger Feinherb'),(172,4,6,91,22.00,'Fritz Haag 2014 Riesling (Mosel)','Just a touch of honey-lemon sweetness is enough to make this zesty, citrus-focused Riesling lip smackingly delicious. Fresh, green herb and lime notes reverberate through a strong finish. Drinks well now but should meld nicely over the next five years.','Germany','Mosel',NULL,NULL,'Fritz Haag',NULL),(173,9,5,91,20.00,'G7 2012 The 7th Generation Gran Reserva Estate Bottled Cabernet Sauvignon (Loncomilla Valley)','Dry, spicy aromas of tobacco, cedar, vanilla and berry fruits come together nicely. This Maule Valley Cab is fresh and harmonious across the palate, with nothing too pushy. Complex, balsamic flavors of olives, herbs, dried berries, turned earth and cocoa finish dry, peppery and elegant. Drink through 2019.','Chile','Loncomilla Valley',NULL,NULL,'G7','The 7th Generation Gran Reserva Estate Bottled'),(174,5,3,91,38.00,'Le Cadeau 2014 Pinot Noir (Willamette Valley)','This wine is bursting with gorgeous cherry fruit, forward and luscious. The tannins are ripe and the acids in perfect proportion, keeping the fruit flavors buoyed upon a textural ride into a lingering finish.','US','Oregon','Willamette Valley','Willamette Valley','Le Cadeau',NULL),(175,20,12,88,19.00,'Stoneleigh 2008 Sauvignon Blanc (Marlborough)','The Stoneleigh style traditionally favors ripeness over herbaceousness, and the 2008 holds true to form, offering up grapefruit and nectarine aromas and an appealing blend of citrus and stone-fruit flavors. It\'s plump and round, yet finishes fresh. Good as an apéritif or with light dishes.','New Zealand','Marlborough',NULL,NULL,'Stoneleigh',NULL),(176,57,9,88,25.00,'Tenuta Peter Sölva & Söhne 2007 De Silva Sauvignon (Alto Adige)','Crisp and fresh with enduring aromas of tomato leaf, citrus, pink grapefruit and white stone, this is textbook Sauvignon from the mountainous Alto Adige region of Italy. Pair it with appetizers or lightly spicy foods.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'Tenuta Peter Sölva & Söhne','De Silva'),(177,15,5,88,50.00,'TerraMater 2006 Unusual Cabernet-Shiraz-Zinfandel Red (Maipo Valley)','Haven\'t seen this unusual combination of grapes in quite some time, and you know what, it\'s much better now than when we last saw it in 2001. This vintage has a nice, almost magnetic nose, while the palate is firm and well structured, with cassis, black cherry, coffee and licorice flavors. It\'s a bit boring on the finish, but the mouthfeel and length are just fine. Fruity, rich and balanced. 325 cases made.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'TerraMater','Unusual Cabernet-Shiraz-Zinfandel'),(178,29,9,88,22.00,'Isole e Olena 2005  Chianti Classico','This Chianti Classico strikes a beautiful balance between elegance and intensity. It has both and its pretty aromas of wild berry, rose, ginger, anise and spice come forth in a continuous, steady manner. It feels bright and lively in the mouth and ends with a touch of piquant spice.','Italy','Tuscany','Chianti Classico',NULL,'Isole e Olena',NULL),(179,47,9,88,25.00,'Kenwood 2005 Jack London Vineyard Syrah (Sonoma Valley)','Black as a moonless night, dense in structure, tannic, bone dry and super-peppery, this Syrah isn\'t offering much relief right now. In all likelihood it will emerge from its cocoon in a few years to offer a wealth of ripe blackberry, currant and carob fruit.','US','California','Sonoma Valley','Sonoma','Kenwood','Jack London Vineyard'),(180,11,2,88,27.00,'La Chablisienne 2006 Les Vénérables Vieilles Vignes  (Chablis)','The impact of 50-year old vines is seen in the concentrated fruit, ripe and full,  in this wine. The flavors are of fresh apricots, edged with green apples and pink grapefruit, a combination that shows both richness and great freshness. The finish is a reminder of the fine acidity in 2006.','France','Burgundy','Chablis',NULL,'La Chablisienne','Les Vénérables Vieilles Vignes'),(181,11,9,88,23.00,'Manzoni 2006 Lucia Highland Vineyard Chardonnay (Santa Lucia Highlands)','This is a strong, oaky Chardonnay. It\'s crisp in acidity and forward in pineapple jam, lemon custard and vanilla meringue flavors. If you like the ripe, California style, it\'s for you.','US','California','Santa Lucia Highlands','Central Coast','Manzoni','Lucia Highland Vineyard'),(182,5,9,88,36.00,'McIntyre Vineyards 2006 Mission Ranch Pinot Noir (Arroyo Seco)','Crisp, coastal acidity dominates this wine, making it mouth-wateringly tart. May be too much for some folks, but it\'s quite elegant, with good cherry, black raspberry and cola flavors enriched with a touch of smoky oak.','US','California','Arroyo Seco','Central Coast','McIntyre Vineyards','Mission Ranch'),(183,58,9,88,NULL,'Abbadia Ardenga 2003 M. Vigna  (Brunello di Montalcino)','Loaded with bold, ripe fruit, exotic spice and leather, this is a simple but genuine expression of Brunello di Montalcino. The wine tastes thick and a bit chunky in the mouth because of its chewy, succulent tannins.','Italy','Tuscany','Brunello di Montalcino',NULL,'Abbadia Ardenga','M. Vigna'),(184,59,5,88,12.00,'Alamos 2007 Torrontés (Salta)','With attractive melon and other tropical aromas, this is a Torrontés that rises above the masses. It smells great and tastes like a pure blend of lychee fruit, tangerine and honeydew melon. The palate feel is smooth and round, and the finish is dry, clean and healthy. It\'s everything that Torrontés should be. Drink now.','Argentina','Other','Salta',NULL,'Alamos',NULL),(185,11,9,88,35.00,'Anaba 2007 Chardonnay (Sonoma Coast)','This is a typical Sonoma Coast Chard in the bright acidity that firms up the ripe, long hangtime flavors. Pineapples, pears, peaches, nectarines and subtle papaya notes are joined with buttercream and cinnamon spices. Drink now.','US','California','Sonoma Coast','Sonoma','Anaba',NULL),(186,36,5,88,15.00,'Apaltagua 2007 Envero Gran Reserva Carmenère (Colchagua Valley)','Composed and structured, with its fair share of richness manifested as raisin and molasses. Interestingly, the palate rings with acidity, resulting in a feel that\'s borderline sharp. But there\'s enough fruit and heft to balance things out, and the flavors of cherry, blackberry and cola are nice. A good example of elevated Carmenère (with 10% Cabernet Sauvignon) that doesn\'t cost an arm and a leg.','Chile','Colchagua Valley',NULL,NULL,'Apaltagua','Envero Gran Reserva'),(187,5,9,88,40.00,'Harrington 2006 Wiley Vineyard Pinot Noir (Anderson Valley)','This is a very rich Pinot whose primary virtue is fruit. It just explodes with delicious cherry jam, red currant, licorice and mocha flavors. Dry and crisply acidic, it\'s a beautiful wine for early drinking.','US','California','Anderson Valley',NULL,'Harrington','Wiley Vineyard'),(188,15,9,88,48.00,'Abbazia Santa Anastasia 2003 Montenero Red (Sicilia)','This is a luminous, mature red wine with thick concentration and huge—almost too much—emphasis on toasted oak. Aromas recall vanilla, spice and coffee, although you will find blueberry and cherry on the finish: It is a blend of Nero d\'Avola, Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot.','Italy','Sicily & Sardinia','Sicilia',NULL,'Abbazia Santa Anastasia','Montenero'),(189,16,5,88,11.00,'Viña Bisquertt 2007 Casa La Joya Reserve Merlot (Colchagua Valley)','Bisquertt usually does well with its value-priced Merlots, and seeing that 2007 was an excellent vintage in Chile, this wine excels in the value price range. The nose is dark and saturated, but pure and inviting. And the palate is ripe and smooth, with spice, plum, blackberry and herb notes, particularly anise. Finishes clean,