uity flavors and a refreshing finish. Though an earlier release might have allowed more primary fruit to show through, the wine offers easygoing but elegant enjoyment.','US','New York','Finger Lakes','Finger Lakes','Hermann J. Wiemer','Blanc de Blanc'),(245,15,5,85,13.00,'J. & F. Lurton 2007 Herederos de François Lurton Villafrance de Duero Red (Vino de la Tierra de Castilla y León)','Simple but well-maded wine with aromas of chewing gum, cherry and blackberry. It\'s a plump, sort of grabby red with sweet raspberry and chocolate flavors followed by a creamy, soft finish. Not much complexity but good fruit and depth. Not the least bit hard to drink. Good mass wine.','Spain','Northern Spain','Vino de la Tierra de Castilla y León',NULL,'J. & F. Lurton','Herederos de François Lurton Villafrance de Duero'),(246,11,5,85,12.00,'Finca Las Moras 2007 Reserve Chardonnay (San Juan)','Not exactly a world-class white wine but at least it smells and tastes like Chardonnay. The nose offers some butter and lemon curd, while the palate is jumpy and tastes like a mix of pear, apple and spice. A fresh, young wine that should be drunk soon.','Argentina','Other','San Juan',NULL,'Finca Las Moras','Reserve'),(247,20,9,85,15.00,'Long Flat 2006 Destinations Sauvignon Blanc (Adelaide Hills)','Juicy and well balanced, this is an admirable effort at the price. Boxwood, grapefruit, lemon and quince notes make for a sophisticated first impression. The palate is straightforward citrus while gooseberry notes pop up on the dry finish. Drink now.','Australia','South Australia','Adelaide Hills',NULL,'Long Flat','Destinations'),(248,16,9,85,25.00,'Work 2004 Reserve Merlot (Sonoma Mountain)','Tasty, with pie-filling cherries, blackberries and currants accented with smoky oak, but a little on the soft side. Fully developed, so drink now.','US','California','Sonoma Mountain','Sonoma','Work','Reserve'),(249,5,3,85,45.00,'Amity 2006 Estate Single Vineyard Pinot Noir (Willamette Valley)','This seems as if i