 and polish.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Luján de Cuyo',NULL,'Cueva de las Manos','Reserve'),(255,34,9,89,45.00,'David Fulton 2008 Petite Sirah (St. Helena)','The winery has a good track record with this bottling, which shows how well Petite Sirah does in the warmer St. Helena appellation of Napa Valley. This \'08 is dryish to moderately sweet in jammy blackberries and blueberries, with a smoked meat, bacon edge. But it\'s also firmly tannic, which provides a framework for the sweetness.','US','California','St. Helena','Napa','David Fulton',NULL),(256,5,7,89,55.00,'Esterlina 2009 Reserva Pinot Noir (Cole Ranch)','Esterlina\'s Pinot is very perfumey, light in body and soul at first, as it gathers steam with a tasty backbone of lush red fruit, spice and plenty of staying power over a meal.','US','California','Cole Ranch',NULL,'Esterlina','Reserva'),(257,72,14,89,20.00,'Goats do Roam Wine Co. 2008 Goat-Roti Syrah-Viognier (Coastal Region)','A good value, this is an easy-pleasing Syrah with vibrant notes of red plum, cherry and blueberry. Fine, dusty tannins reminiscent of cocoa powder and dried crushed berries stay after swallow alongside a hint of sweet smoke flavor.','South Africa','Coastal Region',NULL,NULL,'Goats do Roam Wine Co.','Goat-Roti'),(258,15,14,89,18.00,'Graham Beck 2007 The William Red (Coastal Region)','This approachable Cabernet-based blend, which also has 18% Pinotage, 11% Cab Franc and 2% Shiraz, is a spicy and balanced red with notes of menthol, purple florals, black cherry and berry. With a mouthfeel like crushed velvet, a black pepper finish and an attractive price tag, it\'s a shame only 100 cases were produced.','South Africa','Coastal Region',NULL,NULL,'Graham Beck','The William'),(259,9,14,89,35.00,'Hartenberg 2007 Cabernet Sauvignon (Stellenbosch)','This wine strikes a superb balance between herbaceous, green notes and ripe black fruit, all graced with a kiss of sweet vanilla. Rich blackberry and cassis flavors flood the palate, but then