immediate gratification. Drink now–2014.','US','California','Santa Maria Valley','Central Coast','Byron','Monument'),(265,47,14,89,19.00,'Jardin 2007 Syrah (Stellenbosch)','A good amount of earthy spice, tea leaves and forrest floor lead the way on the nose, but the black cherry and berry fruit aromas follow shortly after with an additional accent of sweet cured meat. Medium weight and lush, the creamy mouth transitions into a finish loaded with sweet spice and bittersweet cocoa.','South Africa','Stellenbosch',NULL,NULL,'Jardin',NULL),(266,11,14,89,40.00,'Jardin 2009 Nine Yards Chardonnay (Stellenbosch)','Fairly intense and flavorful, this Chard expresses assertive aromas and flavors of wood-grilled peaches, buttercream frosting, lemon custard and toasted brioche. Medium weight in the mouth with good balance and a touch of baking spice on the close.','South Africa','Stellenbosch',NULL,NULL,'Jardin','Nine Yards'),(267,15,5,89,14.00,'Kaiken 2008 Corte Malbec-Bonarda-Petit Verdot Red (Mendoza)','For an under-$15 red blend, Corte has it going on. It\'s rich and full, almost syrupy on the nose, with lots of oak, ink and vanilla. Shows power and packs a punch, with dark berry, chocolate and spicy flavors. A little tannic and scratchy, but with structure and framework to spare. Malbec (80%), with Bonarda and Petit Verdot.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Mendoza',NULL,'Kaiken','Corte Malbec-Bonarda-Petit Verdot'),(268,1,9,89,40.00,'Lungarotti 2007 Torre di Giano Vigna il Pino White (Torgiano)','This vineyard-designate blend of Trebbiano and Grechetto opens with a luminous golden color and elegant aromas of stone fruit, citrus, Golden Delicious apple and mature pear. There\'s a pretty hint of vanilla and almond butter at the back.','Italy','Central Italy','Torgiano',NULL,'Lungarotti','Torre di Giano Vigna il Pino'),(269,1,9,89,36.00,'Marchesi Fumanelli 2005 Terso White (Veneto)','This sophisticated white wine from the homeland of Italy\'s most robust reds (Ripasso and Amarone) shows a full, generous appearance with a golden-amber color. Stone fruit, toasted almond and candied lemon give it heft and consistency.','Italy','Veneto','Veneto',NULL,'Marchesi Fumanelli','Terso'),(270,73,2,89,17.00,'Mariell 2009 Blaufränkisch (Leithaberg)','Smooth and ripe, this is a rich black-fruited wine, its tannins comfortably ensconsed in a rich cushion. There is acidity to balance and spice which, along with the full-bodied fruit character, makes the wine ready to drink now.','Austria','Leithaberg',NULL,NULL,'Mariell',NULL),(271,74,9,89,25.00,'Livio Felluga 2009 Friulano (Colli Orientali del Friuli)','A gorgeous expression of Friulano, this wine (in a screwcap bottle) makes an elegant addition to chicken, pasta or seafood dinners. Layers of peach, almond and pineapple are wrapped tightly together.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Colli Orientali del Friuli',NULL,'Livio Felluga',NULL),(272,75,16,89,15.00,'My Big Fat Greek Wine 2010 Assyrtico (Santorini)','Lively aromas of lemon, grapefruit and melon start this white from Greece. Flavors of grapefruit and lemon rind are fresh and crisp but still offer dimension. The finish is spicy and clean. A great food wine: pair with grilled fish or clams.','Greece','Santorini',NULL,NULL,'My Big Fat Greek Wine',NULL),(273,65,9,89,26.00,'Nals Margreid 2010 Sirmian Pinot Bianco (Alto Adige)','This partially oak-aged expression of Pinot Bianco from cool-climate Alto Adige (in the far north of Italy) offers a lovely texture that is creamy and smooth at the same time. Measured aromas include melon, apricot, grapefruit and a touch of vanilla spice.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'Nals Margreid','Sirmian'),(274,15,5,89,19.00,'O. Fournier 2007 B Crux Red (Uco Valley)','Leather, berry, earth, raisin and roasted qualities define the nose on this Tempranillo-led blend of four grapes. Feels good in the mouth, with active raspberry, plum and coffee flavors that comes with a roasted accent. Mildly leafy, baked and woody on the thorough finish.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Uco Valley',NULL,'O. Fournier','B Crux'),(275,1,9,89,13.00,'Pico Maccario 2010 Estrosa White (Monferrato)','This is a gorgeous Italian white from northern Italy that boasts fragrant tones of spring flower and chopped herb backed by peach, honey and white almond. It\'s crisp, intense and would be perfect with basil Thai curry.','Italy','Piedmont','Monferrato',NULL,'Pico Maccario','Estrosa'),(276,9,5,89,30.00,'Sottano 2009 Reserva de Familia Cabernet Sauvignon (Mendoza)','A medium-weight Cabernet with plum, prune, tobacco and herb aromas. Features average weight and body, with a creamy texture and layered flavors of black fruit, raspberry and spice. Finishes with herb and plum notes as well as a pinch of tobacco.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Mendoza',NULL,'Sottano','Reserva de Familia'),(277,40,9,89,20.00,'St. Francis 2009 Old Vines Zinfandel (Sonoma County)','A huge, kick butt Zinfandel, packed with sweet berry, bacon, black pepper and smoky cedar flavors. There\'s absolutely nothing shy about it. Packs a real punch all the way through to the spicy finish. Good price for a Sonoma Zin this classic.','US','California','Sonoma County','Sonoma','St. Francis','Old Vines'),(278,9,9,89,30.00,'Trailhead 2010 Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','Quite a good Cabernet, showing the elegance and ripe fruitiness you expect from Napa, in a style for drinking now. Drily tannic, it shows classic blackberry and blueberry flavors.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Trailhead',NULL),(279,5,3,89,50.00,'Erath 2009 Bishop Creek Pinot Noir','Fruity, forward and quite refreshing, this has appealing black cherry fruit with a light candy flavor. The balancing tannins add sufficient depth and weight to allow this a few more years in the cellar.','US','Oregon','Willamette Valley',NULL,'Erath','Bishop Creek'),(280,57,9,89,52.00,'Franz Haas 2009 Sauvignon (Alto Adige)','This oak-fermented Sauvignon (in an artsy, screwcap bottle) delivers a rich, spicy finish and thick layers of peach, citrus, tomato leaf and honey-like aromas. It\'s a gorgeous wine that is an absolute pleasure to drink.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'Franz Haas',NULL),(281,43,2,92,24.00,'Forstreiter 2012 Schiefer Reserve Grüner Veltliner (Kremstal)','A strongly spicy, rich wine, this has great concentration and an intense, dense texture.There is weight with plenty of ripe tropical fruits to contrast pronounced black pepper and bitter almond character. It\'s still young, so don\'t drink before 2015. Screwcap.','Austria','Kremstal',NULL,NULL,'Forstreiter','Schiefer Reserve'),(282,5,9,92,34.00,'Cambria 2011 Bench Break Vineyard Pinot Noir (Santa Maria Valley)','This is another fine Pinot from Cambria, showing the winery\'s great price-quality ratio. Words like opulent and elegant come to mind to describe intense flavors of black cherries, licorice, cola, herb tea and Indian spices. It\'s bone dry, and also quite tannic, but you can enjoy it now with big, rich lamb and beef dishes, or a wild mushroom risotto. Otherwise, it will continue to improve for at least eight years.','US','California','Santa Maria Valley','Central Coast','Cambria','Bench Break Vineyard'),(283,15,1,92,41.00,'I Giusti e Zanza 2009 Dulcamara Red (Toscana)','This delicious blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot and Petit Verdot opens with an intense, brooding fragrance of dark fruit, spice and leather. The palate delivers a concentrated black-cherry flavor that\'s framed by big, chewy tannins and  punctuated by spicy accents of white and black pepper, licorice and pipe. Drink 2015–2024.','Italy','Tuscany','Toscana',NULL,'I Giusti e Zanza','Dulcamara'),(284,5,3,92,52.00,'J. Christopher 2011 Bella Vida Vineyard Unfiltered Pinot Noir (Dundee Hills)','Bella Vida replaces the Abbey Ridge bottling and does so with pizzazz. The best of the 2011 releases, this is a beautiful expression of grapes grown on red clay soils, with refined, deeply penetrating flavors of ripe raspberries. Smooth, supple and long, with uncommon purity, it finishes with a kiss of chocolate from 18 months in one-quarter new oak barrels.','US','Oregon','Dundee Hills','Willamette Valley','J. Christopher','Bella Vida Vineyard Unfiltered'),(285,12,5,92,215.00,'Viña Cobos 2011 Marchiori Vineyard Block C2 Malbec (Perdriel)','This huge Malbec defines jammy and concentrated. The bouquet is ripe, soft and minty, while the palate echoes the nose with thickness and density. Flavors of prune, raisin, tea and blackberry are borderline syrupy, while the finish is smooth and pure but doesn\'t offer much spine or foundation. Drink this modern Malbec sooner rather than later.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Perdriel',NULL,'Viña Cobos','Marchiori Vineyard Block C2'),(286,4,2,92,NULL,'Salomon-Undhof 2011 Steiner Kögl Erste Lage Riesling (Kremstal)','This is a very aromatic wine that\'s rich, spicy and with just a touch of ripeness. It has spiced pear, lychee and honey notes all balanced by a wonderful fresh acidity. Drink now and until 2020. Screwcap.','Austria','Kremstal',NULL,NULL,'Salomon-Undhof','Steiner Kögl Erste Lage'),(287,5,9,92,60.00,'Talley 2011 Rincon Vineyard Pinot Noir (Arroyo Grande Valley)','While delicious now with flavors of raspberries, cherries, cola and oak, all showered with tart, citrusy acidity, this wine also has a great future. Give it 6–8 years to evolve in the bottle for further complexity.','US','California','Arroyo Grande Valley','Central Coast','Talley','Rincon Vineyard'),(288,76,5,92,40.00,'Acústic 2010 Braó Vinyes Velles Carignan-Grenache (Montsant)','This is the stud in the Acústic stable. A blend of 70% Carignan and 30% Garnacha, Braó is lively and bright on the nose, with ripe blackberry and cassis aromas. The palate is concentrated and juicy, with fine balance and bold flavors of blueberry, blackberry and coffee. A toasty, dark finish features chocolate, toast and minerality. Drink through 2019.','Spain','Catalonia','Montsant',NULL,'Acústic','Braó Vinyes Velles'),(289,43,2,92,NULL,'Josef Schmid 2011 Kremser Gebling Erste Lage Grüner Veltliner (Kremstal)','While it feels rich and round, this is also a wine with a crisp side to it. Acidity cuts through ripe pear, apricot and lychee flavors, giving a decidedly crisp balance. It\'s a wine that is already ready to drink. Screwcap.','Austria','Kremstal',NULL,NULL,'Josef Schmid','Kremser Gebling Erste Lage'),(290,9,9,92,125.00,'Parallel 2010 Fortune Teller Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','This 100% Cabernet Sauvignon is so rich and decadent, with milk chocolate, blackberry and new French oak flavors. Made by celebrity winemaker Philippe Melka, it\'s soft and approacheable on the palate and widely appealing. Your best bet is to drink up now.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Parallel','Fortune Teller'),(291,32,2,92,NULL,'Château Lafon-Rochet 2011  Saint-Estèphe','This is a wine that has great potential—you can tell from the firm tannins, tight acidity and closed texture. Initially, black currant flavors are touched with dark, dusty notes, but they finish with more juicy character on the afterntaste. Drink from 2017.','France','Bordeaux','Saint-Estèphe',NULL,'Château Lafon-Rochet',NULL),(292,77,1,92,NULL,'Dionigi 2006  Sagrantino di Montefalco','This powerful Sagrantino opens with aromas of meat juice, truffle and black fruit. The palate offers blackberry, black cherry, cinnamon and black pepper, along with tobacco notes. It also has Sagrantino\'s trademark tannic backbone, but the tannins are ripe and are balanced by bright acidity.','Italy','Central Italy','Sagrantino di Montefalco',NULL,'Dionigi',NULL),(293,78,2,92,45.00,'Domaine Daniel Dugois 2006 Vin Jaune Savagnin (Arbois)','Rich almonds, ripe peaches and a smoky, oxidized character all come together in this ripe, complex, fascinating wine. There is a great tang of apple acidity on the finish. Drink now.','France','France Other','Arbois',NULL,'Domaine Daniel Dugois','Vin Jaune'),(294,67,12,92,70.00,'Kilikanoon 2009 Green\'s Vineyard Shiraz (Barossa Valley)','This wine displays ample concentration in its inky color and potent aromas of dark berry fruit. There\'s a hint of raisining as well. In the mouth, it\'s mouthfilling but lacks a bit of texture; the flavors include dark plums, vanilla and hints of dried fruits, like figs and dates. With a finish that calls to mind chocolate fudge (minus the sugar), opt for drinking this wine over the relatively near term, now to 2020.','Australia','South Australia','Barossa Valley',NULL,'Kilikanoon','Green\'s Vineyard'),(295,12,5,92,30.00,'Finca Sophenia 2011 Synthesis Malbec (Tupungato)','Deep, lush aromas of black fruits, graphite and coconut are welcoming and friendly. The mouthfeel is pure and smooth, with elegance and power. Flavors of cassis, blackberry, hard spices and licorice filter into a long, mellow, classy finish. This is a pushy, full-bodied wine that doesn\'t throw punches; drink through 2020.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Tupungato',NULL,'Finca Sophenia','Synthesis'),(296,79,9,87,35.00,'Treana 2008 Treana Red Cabernet Sauvignon-Syrah (Paso Robles)','This blend showcases the soft lusciousness and ripe fruit of Paso Robles. It\'s rich and sweet in jammy blackberries, cherries, chocolate and spicy sandalwood. Drink now.','US','California','Paso Robles','Central Coast','Treana','Treana Red'),(297,9,5,87,20.00,'Ventisquero 2008 Grey [Glacier] Single Block Trinidad Vineyard Cabernet Sauvignon (Maipo Valley)','Rooty and leafy on the nose, with red berry aromas peeking through some obvious oak. The palate offers cherry and raspberry flavors along with sweetness, and things are backed by vanilla and chocolate. Good, tasty and oaky, with proper layering.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'Ventisquero','Grey [Glacier] Single Block Trinidad Vineyard'),(298,9,9,87,15.00,'Aquinas 2008 Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','This is a soft, gentle Cabernet for drinking now. It\'s pleasantly rich, offering blackberry, cherry, chocolate and cedar flavors, wrapped into easy tannins.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Aquinas',NULL),(299,9,5,87,19.00,'Arboleda 2009 Cabernet Sauvignon (Aconcagua Valley)','Foresty and dark on the bouquet, with aromas of licorice, prune, forest and foxiness. The palate is full and tannic, while flavors run sweet, creamy and slightly syrupy, with chocolate and spiced fig notes. Finishes rich and rough, with dry herbs and true Chilean Cab flavors of olive and oregano.','Chile','Aconcagua Valley',NULL,NULL,'Arboleda',NULL),(300,15,9,87,NULL,'Attilio Ghisolfi 2007 Pinay Red (Langhe)','Pinay is a tight and defined red blend from northern Italy with bright accents of cherry cola, forest berry, licorice and dark mineral. There\'s a sharp, sour note on the close that would pair with smoked cheese.','Italy','Piedmont','Langhe',NULL,'Attilio Ghisolfi','Pinay'),(301,29,9,87,28.00,'Benessere 2007 Estate Sangiovese (Napa Valley)','Soft, light in body and easy to drink, this Sangiovese, from the Napa estate vineyard, is delicious in raspberry, red currant, licorice, bacon and spice flavors. It\'s somewhat ephemeral, an instantly pleasant wine to drink especially with cured meats, olives, hard cheeses.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Benessere','Estate'),(302,11,3,87,14.00,'Buried Cane 2009 Whiteline No Oak Chardonnay (Columbia Valley (WA))','A good, clean, tart and lightly spicy all-stainless style. Cool climate fruit puts the accent on lime and lemon flavors, keeps the alcohol low (13.3%), and makes this a fine match to shellfish, white fish and light pasta dishes.','US','Washington','Columbia Valley (WA)','Columbia Valley','Buried Cane','Whiteline No Oak'),(303,48,9,87,NULL,'Cantina del Nebbiolo 2008  Roero','This fresh Nebbiolo-based Roero from Cantina dei Nebbiolo offers pretty intensity with aromas of tar, licorice and a touch of sweet cherry liqueur. There isn\'t much pulp or meat here but the finish is both crisp and tart.','Italy','Piedmont','Roero',NULL,'Cantina del Nebbiolo',NULL),(304,48,9,87,56.00,'Cascina Adelaide 2005 4 Vigne  (Barolo)','Slightly disjointed at first, this Barolo with fruit sourced from four vineyard sites, needs a few minutes to open in the glass. The wine offers tertiary aromas of cured beef, smoked bacon and white mushroom. Drink now.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Cascina Adelaide','4 Vigne'),(305,52,9,87,NULL,'Cascina La Ghersa 2004 Vignassa  (Barbera d\'Asti Superiore Nizza)','This aged expression from the Nizza subzone of Asti offers tertiary aromas of dried tobacco and dried prune. The variety\'s characteristic acidity kicks in on the finish.','Italy','Piedmont','Barbera d\'Asti Superiore Nizza',NULL,'Cascina La Ghersa','Vignassa'),(306,40,7,87,24.00,'Claudia Springs 2007 Zinfandel (Mendocino County)','Muted at first, this wine opens up nicely with time. Sweet, ripe and easy on the finish, its core is full of black pepper and clove. The grapes are sourced from several distinctive vineyards in Mendocino County. Drink it with a steak.','US','California','Mendocino County',NULL,'Claudia Springs',NULL),(307,11,6,87,7.00,'Cramele Recas 2009 Chardonnay (Recas)','Fragrant on the nose with fresh orange, lemon and honeysuckle aromas, this full-bodied Chard is deliciously quaffable with a concentrated apple palate and just a hint of buttered toast. Another well-made Romanian at an unbeatable bargain price.','Romania','Recas',NULL,NULL,'Cramele Recas',NULL),(308,5,2,87,30.00,'Domaine Bertagna 2009 Les Dames Huguettes  (Côte de Nuits-Villages)','Rich and full in the mouth, packed with red fruits and black cherries. The wine is sweet, while keeping a tannic core. Drink next year.','France','Burgundy','Côte de Nuits-Villages',NULL,'Domaine Bertagna','Les Dames Huguettes'),(309,1,16,87,18.00,'Domaine Sigalas 2010 Asirtiko Athiri White (Santorini)','This fuller-bodied white blend offers pineapple, kiwi and citrus on the nose, and a blend of full fruit and acidity on the palate. A balanced, easygoing white that is perfect for everyday poultry, vegetable and fish meals.','Greece','Santorini',NULL,NULL,'Domaine Sigalas','Asirtiko Athiri'),(310,48,9,87,20.00,'Socré 2006 Nebbiolo (Langhe)','Here\'s a fun and slightly less formal expression of Nebbiolo (especially when compared to the great wines of Barbaresco and Barolo) that offers tight fruit nuances of white cherry and forest berry backed by light shadings of spice and smoke.','Italy','Piedmont','Langhe',NULL,'Socré',NULL),(311,48,9,87,18.00,'Boffa 2006 Nebbiolo (Langhe)','Aged 12 months in large oak casks, this bright Nebbiolo offers pretty aromas of small berry, tar, licorice and cigar smoke backed by tight intensity and structure. Pair this powerful wine with braised quail or pork tenderloin.','Italy','Piedmont','Langhe',NULL,'Boffa',NULL),(312,47,12,87,18.00,'Otto\'s Constant Dream 2008 Syrah (Hawke\'s Bay)','This wine is light in color, but still packs a mouthful of flavor. It\'s peppery and meaty upfront, filled out on the midpalate by tart fruit that verges on cranberry in flavor. Pretty rather than potent; drink now-2014.','New Zealand','Hawke\'s Bay',NULL,NULL,'Otto\'s Constant Dream',NULL),(313,9,9,87,40.00,'Mount Veeder 2008 Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','A good wine to drink now for its sweet, ripe berry and mocha flavors and smoky coat of oak. It has smooth tannins and a spicy finish. Give it a good decant to let it breathe for a few hours.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Mount Veeder',NULL),(314,48,9,87,NULL,'Rabino 2008  Roero','Roero Rabino is accented by sweet touches of cinnamon and nutmeg that are offset by cassis, dried blueberry, leather and tobacco. This sturdy red wine presents a very nice ensemble that is capped by a tight, astringent close.','Italy','Piedmont','Roero',NULL,'Rabino',NULL),(315,9,9,87,28.00,'Robert Mondavi 2008 Cabernet Sauvignon (Napa Valley)','With rich, sweet blackberry and cocoa flavors, this is a very nice Cabernet for drinking with a good meal. It\'s a little rough around the edges, with jaggy tannins. Ready now.','US','California','Napa Valley','Napa','Robert Mondavi',NULL),(316,80,9,86,15.00,'Bellussi NV Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','Honey, almond blossom and citrus zest are followed by creamy foam and tonic acidity. This is an easygoing Prosecco that offers a light and compact structure and bright flavors of lime and green fruit.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Bellussi','Extra Dry'),(317,27,2,86,NULL,'Château Mont-Pérat 2008 Les Amants Mont-Pérat  (Bordeaux Blanc)','An intriguing blend of Sauvignon Blanc and Muscadelle, which highlights the herbaceous Sauvignon character and a more perfumed Muscadelle. The two give a fresh, citrus- and pineapple-flavored wine, lively, to be enjoyed young.','France','Bordeaux','Bordeaux Blanc',NULL,'Château Mont-Pérat','Les Amants Mont-Pérat'),(318,27,2,86,NULL,'Château Tour de Mirambeau 2006  Bordeaux Blanc','Soft, ripe, dominated by peaches, pears and a rounded, toasty character. The spice is dominant, giving the wine an exotic edge. The more rounded style gives concentration as well as a fine, finishing velvet texture.','France','Bordeaux','Bordeaux Blanc',NULL,'Château Tour de Mirambeau',NULL),(319,16,5,86,18.00,'Aresti 2007 Reserva Merlot (Curicó Valley)','Fiery and wild at first, with aromas of cinnamon, pepper and Juicy Fruit gum. Strange as that may sound, the wine finds a more familiar place on the palate, where plum, cherry and cassis flavors are flashy and the feel is a bit clangy. Rounds out with air and settles down fairly nicely.','Chile','Curicó Valley',NULL,NULL,'Aresti','Reserva'),(320,80,9,86,20.00,'Paladin 2007 Millesimato Brut Prosecco (Veneto)','Paladin produces a luminous and fresh Prosecco from the northeast of Italy with tonic aromas of peach, white stone and citrus fruit. It\'s an easy-drinking wine that would wash down well with appetizers and informal finger foods.','Italy','Veneto','Veneto',NULL,'Paladin','Millesimato Brut'),(321,80,9,86,22.00,'Perlage 2008 Col di Manza Extra Dry Millesimato  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','Soapy aromas of bee\'s wax and lavender open the nose of this luminous sparkler and are followed by dried flowers and hay. There are peach-like flavors with aftertastes of green melon and lime. Grapes are grown organically and according to biodynamic principles.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Perlage','Col di Manza Extra Dry Millesimato'),(322,80,9,86,16.00,'Sant Eurosia 2007 Brut  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','This Brut interpretation of Prosecco (“Brut” means it tastes dry in the mouth) offers tangy fizz and soda-like intensity backed by subdued aromas of white mineral and stone fruit. Pair it with puff pastry appetizers.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Sant Eurosia','Brut'),(323,80,9,86,18.00,'Sant Eurosia 2007 Millesimato Dry  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','This is a “dry” vintage Prosecco with a hint of sweetness in the mouth that is surrounded by fragrant flavors of peach, kiwi and green melon. This luminous sparkler tastes firm and tonic and makes for an informal afternoon sipper.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Sant Eurosia','Millesimato Dry'),(324,9,5,86,35.00,'J. & F. Lurton 2006 Gran Araucano Cabernet Sauvignon (Colchagua Valley)','Mildly minty and woody on the nose, with grass, wintergreen and cheese aromas as well as red fruit. The palate is tight and grabby, with a blast of citric acid that gives the plum and raspberry flavors a tart, decidedly “red” personality. Snappy and crisp on the finish, making it a fresh, lean style of Cabernet.','Chile','Colchagua Valley',NULL,NULL,'J. & F. Lurton','Gran Araucano'),(325,80,9,86,12.00,'L\'Antica Quercia 2007 Matiú Brut  (Prosecco di Conegliano)','The wine\'s golden hue tells you this is Prosecco from a warmer climate (Conegliano is a few degrees warmer than Valdobbiadene) as do its aromas of mature peach and honeysuckle. The wine tastes flat and big in the mouth and offers sophisticated notes of white pepper and spice.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Conegliano',NULL,'L\'Antica Quercia','Matiú Brut'),(326,81,16,86,11.00,'Lucas Vineyards 2007 Vignoles (Finger Lakes)','This white has a light, delicate nose of citrus and apricot. On the palate it\'s smooth and balanced with lush apricot and spice flavors. A touch of acidity gives the wine lift. A lingering finish adds to its poise. Pair with a creamy cheese or sip alone.','US','New York','Finger Lakes','Finger Lakes','Lucas Vineyards',NULL),(327,80,9,86,15.00,'Marsuret NV Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','Drying mineral tones face off with luscious peach flavors to create a well-balanced Extra Dry Prosecco sparkler. The bubbly offers cheerful foaming in the mouth and sweet fruit flavors on the close.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Marsuret','Extra Dry'),(328,11,5,86,18.00,'De Martino 2007 Legado Reserva Chardonnay (Limarí Valley)','Opening aromas of vanilla cookie show a resemblance to Animal Crackers, while the palate is more vivacious and tangy, with flavors of orange, tangerine and apple. We wouldn\'t call this an elegant or refined wine, but we like its no-issues attitude and citrusy content. Probably good with salads and seafood.','Chile','Limarí Valley',NULL,NULL,'De Martino','Legado Reserva'),(329,1,9,86,16.00,'Beringer 2007 Alluvium Blanc White (Knights Valley)','This New World blend of Sauvignon Blanc, Sémillon, Chardonnay and Viognier is very fruity. It offers a blast of pineapples, honeysuckles, peaches and figs, with a coating of oaky, vanilla buttercream.','US','California','Knights Valley','Sonoma','Beringer','Alluvium Blanc'),(330,40,9,86,34.00,'Brutocao 2006 Reserve Zinfandel (Mendocino)','With a fruity-sugary finish, this Zin will appeal to folks who like their red wines a little on the sweet side. It has pleasantly ripe flavors of black cherries, raspberries, red currants, root beer, mocha and pepper.','US','California','Mendocino',NULL,'Brutocao','Reserve'),(331,15,9,86,40.00,'Clos La Chance 2006 Lila\'s Cuvée Red (Central Coast)','This Rhône-style blend is a little rustic and sharp in tannins and acids. It shows a polished core of jammy blackberries, cherries and spices, and could develop in a year or two.','US','California','Central Coast','Central Coast','Clos La Chance','Lila\'s Cuvée'),(332,8,5,86,15.00,'Cono Sur 2008 Visión Gewürztraminer (Casablanca Valley)','Frosted aromas of orange creamsicle, lychee and melon give this an elevated, unique sort of bouquet. Among Chilean Gewürztraminers, this is one of the more expressive ones you\'ll find. Pineapple, mango and other tropical flavors are pleasant, while the feel is forward and fun. Drink this summer with fish and salads.','Chile','Casablanca Valley',NULL,NULL,'Cono Sur','Visión'),(333,80,9,86,19.00,'Sommariva NV Palazzo Rosso Brut  (Prosecco di Conegliano)','This Prosecco Brut from the slightly warmer Conegliano subzone is a perfect example of its kind. The luminous sparkler offers drying mineral tones that are embellished by pretty notes of white rose, honey, stone fruit and citrus. The mouthfeel is lean, smooth and fresh.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Conegliano',NULL,'Sommariva','Palazzo Rosso Brut'),(334,80,9,86,18.00,'Spagnol NV Col del Sas Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','This crisp sparkler is characterized by drying mineral tones and delicate aromas of stone fruit and citrus. The wine is foamy and slightly sweet in the mouth and does an excellent job of representing this category of Italian wine.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Spagnol','Col del Sas Extra Dry'),(335,31,2,86,42.00,'Jacquart NV Mosaïque Rosé Brut  (Champagne)','A ripe, fruity wine that takes its raspberry flavor from the color. The wine has softness, a creamy character that rounds out any acidity, leaving a smooth, fruity finish.','France','Champagne','Champagne',NULL,'Jacquart','Mosaïque Rosé Brut'),(336,80,9,86,15.00,'L\'Antica Quercia 2007 Arió Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Conegliano)','There\'s a unique note here of mature fruit, chopped basil or peppermint with a hint of spice or chopped white peppercorn. The bubbling seems less frothy and the wine has a flat, big feel in the mouth. Grapes were farmed organically and the wine is from the 2007 vintage, which may explain its distinctive style.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Conegliano',NULL,'L\'Antica Quercia','Arió Extra Dry'),(337,5,5,83,35.00,'Koyle 2015 Costa Pinot Noir (Colchagua Costa)','Gritty, heavily roasted aromas of peanuts and herbal berry fruits lead to a scratchy, tannic palate. This tastes of burnt oak, raw plum and currant, while the finish tastes briny and harsh. The 2012 version of this wine was much better. This is rough from front to back.','Chile','Colchagua Costa',NULL,NULL,'Koyle','Costa'),(338,39,14,83,16.00,'Château Notre Dame du Quatourze 2015 Rosé (Languedoc)','An easy and inviting selection, there\'s a mentholated streak to the soft red currant and cherry core of this wine. Light and breezy on the palate, it offers thin, quickly dissipating flavors and a fleeting finish.','France','Languedoc-Roussillon','Languedoc',NULL,'Château Notre Dame du Quatourze',NULL),(339,39,2,82,11.00,'Mémoires 2015 Rosé (Coteaux Varois en Provence)','The wine is earthy and somewhat rustic. There is fruit but it is spoiled by a spicy pepper edge. Chill this drastically.','France','Provence','Coteaux Varois en Provence',NULL,'Mémoires',NULL),(340,82,5,82,13.00,'Cavas Hill NV 1887 Rosado Sparkling (Cava)','Red in color, with berry and apple aromas, this is sweet, with a heavy body and light effervescence.','Spain','Catalonia','Cava',NULL,'Cavas Hill','1887 Rosado'),(341,3,13,82,18.00,'Antoine Moltès & Fils 2015 Tradition Pinot Gris (Alsace)','The nose is muted, despite the slight spritz of the wine, while the palate is equally toned down. It\'s a rounded if not very expressive white wine.','France','Alsace','Alsace',NULL,'Antoine Moltès & Fils','Tradition'),(342,40,7,82,48.00,'Pezzi King 2013 Serracino Reserve Zinfandel (Dry Creek Valley)','Plummy and hinting at black cherry, this wine is otherwise soft and simple, with a distracting, full-throttled descent into raisin cake and prune.','US','California','Dry Creek Valley','Sonoma','Pezzi King','Serracino Reserve'),(343,82,5,82,11.00,'Bellisco NV Sparkling (Cava)','Funky, yeasty aromas of cinnamon, spent lees and bread yeast dominate the nose. This feels foamy, with lightly vegetal flavors of apple that finish briny.','Spain','Catalonia','Cava',NULL,'Bellisco',NULL),(344,5,5,81,20.00,'Pura 8 2010 Grand Reserve Pinot Noir (Rapel Valley)','Jumpy on the nose at first, but then green tea and grassy aromas take over. This PN is what it is: it tastes grassy, leafy and like green beans. Vegetal notes carry over to the finish.','Chile','Rapel Valley',NULL,NULL,'Pura 8','Grand Reserve'),(345,11,5,80,19.00,'Viña Tarapacá 2015 Gran Reserva Chardonnay (Leyda Valley)','Aromas of pumpkin, squash and corn chips are stale and not inviting. There\'s an acceptable mouthfeel to this weird, unbalanced Chardonnay along with flavors of spiced squash, mealy apple and sautéed root vegetables.','Chile','Leyda Valley',NULL,NULL,'Viña Tarapacá','Gran Reserva'),(346,83,12,100,350.00,'Chambers Rosewood Vineyards NV Rare Muscat (Rutherglen)','This wine contains some material over 100 years old, but shows no signs of fragility. Instead, it\'s concentrated through age and should hold in the bottle indefinitely. It\'s dark coffee-brown in color, with delectable aromas of rancio, dried fig, molasses and black tea, yet despite enormous concentration avoids excessive weight. And it\'s amazingly complex and fresh on the nearly endless finish.','Australia','Victoria','Rutherglen',NULL,'Chambers Rosewood Vineyards','Rare'),(347,84,12,98,350.00,'Chambers Rosewood Vineyards NV Rare Muscadelle (Rutherglen)','This deep brown wine smells like a damp, mossy cave. Then add complex rancio notes, plus maple syrup and molasses. It\'s full, round and harmonious, wonderfully rich yet without any sense of heaviness and long and bright on the finish.','Australia','Victoria','Rutherglen',NULL,'Chambers Rosewood Vineyards','Rare'),(348,4,6,97,775.00,'Robert Weil 2014 Kiedrich Gräfenberg Trockenbeerenauslese Riesling (Rheingau)','Dusty, saffron-spiced earthiness is juxtaposed against intense mango and tangerine fruitiness in this deeply complex wine. It\'s unctuously sweet, but balanced by a piercing streak of acidity that penetrates through the midpalate. Spry and silken, it finishes on a long lingering whisper of honey and peach.','Germany','Rheingau',NULL,NULL,'Robert Weil','Kiedrich Gräfenberg Trockenbeerenauslese'),(349,83,12,97,100.00,'Chambers Rosewood Vineyards NV Grand Muscat (Rutherglen)','Deep mahogany. Dried fig and black tea on the nose, then concentrated mocha and molasses flavors, enlivened by candied orange zest. Full, rich and sweet, but surprisingly drinkable, with terrific intensity and length.','Australia','Victoria','Rutherglen',NULL,'Chambers Rosewood Vineyards','Grand'),(350,85,12,97,225.00,'Torbreck 2012 RunRig Shiraz-Viognier (Barossa)','RunRig is always complex, and the 2012 doesn\'t disappoint in that regard, mixing bacony-meaty notes with hints of black olives and ripe plums. The tannins are supremely supple, but the acids are crisp, resulting in a long, mouthwatering finish. Drink now–2030.','Australia','South Australia','Barossa',NULL,'Torbreck','RunRig'),(351,48,1,97,150.00,'Cavallotto 2010 Vignolo Riserva  (Barolo)','After a few minutes in the glass, this stunning wine opens up to reveal classic Nebbiolo aromas of leather, tilled soil, underbrush, fragrant blue flower and ripe berry. The juicy concentrated palate dishes out layers of succulent black cherry, crushed raspberry, anise and pipe tobacco framed in firm, velvety tannins. Drink 2022–2035.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Cavallotto','Vignolo Riserva'),(352,64,15,96,320.00,'Oremus 2005 Eszencia  (Tokaji)','This amber-colored Hungarian stunner has ethereal aromas of raw honey, beeswax, freshly baked tarte Tatin, canned apricot and fresh pear. It is silky smooth and creamy in the mouth with pronounced flavors of clover honey, pear tart and baked sweet apples. The acidity is perfectly balanced so you can appreciate its velvety richness without feeling that the sweetness is too cloying.','Hungary','Tokaji',NULL,NULL,'Oremus','Eszencia'),(353,11,7,96,68.00,'Rochioli 2014 South River Chardonnay (Russian River Valley)','Citrus-kissed saltiness lies at the core of this incredibly delicious, deliriously crafted wine, from the great grape grower in the heart of the Russian River Valley. Beautifully crisp, it lingers in stony minerality and a freshness of apricot, memorable from first sip to last.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Rochioli','South River'),(354,11,2,96,630.00,'Louis Latour 2014 Le Montrachet  (Montrachet)','This beautiful, rich wine has yellow fruits and is concentrated, tightly textured and conveys a ripe character. The touches of wood are just right, adding spice to the opulent fruitiness. A mineral texture gives some tightness to the aftertaste. Drink from 2024.','France','Burgundy','Montrachet',NULL,'Louis Latour','Le Montrachet'),(355,4,6,96,365.00,'Robert Weil 2014 Kiedrich Gräfenberg Beerenauslese Riesling (Rheingau)','Whiffs of white mushroom, saffron and caramel lend complexity to this concentrated elixir of apricots and orange peels. It\'s honeyed and sweet but vivaciously balanced, glazing the palate in ethereal textures of gossamer and tulle. The caramel finish lingers endlessly.','Germany','Rheingau',NULL,NULL,'Robert Weil','Kiedrich Gräfenberg Beerenauslese'),(356,11,7,96,68.00,'Rochioli 2014 Sweetwater Chardonnay (Russian River Valley)','A waft of smoky char and toasty oak provide a rich foundation and compelling entry into this one-acre vineyard-designate from the historic grower, before unleashing, slowly, a torrent of melon and fresh-cut apple with a length of intriguing nutmeg and cardamom. Medium-bodied and lush, it will remain on your palate memory a long time.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Rochioli','Sweetwater'),(357,67,12,95,85.00,'Jasper Hill 2013 Georgia\'s Paddock Shiraz (Heathcote)','Dusty, firm, powerful: just a few apt descriptors for this vintage of one of Heathcote\'s top wines. Mocha, licorice and blackberries feature on the nose, while the palate delivers more of the same—dark fruit, chocolate and plenty of spice. Best after 2020.','Australia','Victoria','Heathcote',NULL,'Jasper Hill','Georgia\'s Paddock'),(358,5,2,95,350.00,'Château de la Tour 2013 Vieilles Vignes  (Clos de Vougeot)','Produced from vines more than 100 years old in the heart of the Clos de Vougeot vineyard, this is an impressive wine with a long future. The wood aging is already surrounded by ripe, intense black fruits. A fresher character comes from the bright acidity of the vintage, giving the wine a lift. The aftertaste is long and concentrated. Drink from 2024.','France','Burgundy','Clos de Vougeot',NULL,'Château de la Tour','Vieilles Vignes'),(359,4,6,95,66.00,'Weingut Hans Bausch 2011 Hattenheimer Hassel Auslese Riesling (Rheingau)','Intensely fragrant, this honey-sweet auslese wafts of ripe yellow peaches and caramelized sugar. Tropical mango, pineapple and melon collide on the palate before falling neatly in line against a strike of high-toned acidity. The finish is luxuriously long, peppered by a faint dusting of saffron. It\'s a stunner already but should shine brightly for decades to come.','Germany','Rheingau',NULL,NULL,'Weingut Hans Bausch','Hattenheimer Hassel Auslese'),(360,11,2,95,110.00,'Philippe Colin 2014 Les Chenevottes Premier Cru  (Chassagne-Montrachet)','Up the slope above the Grand Cru of Le Montrachet, this vineyard once grew hemp (hence the name, cheneve). This poised wine is both stylish and rich, with good acidity allied to ripe apple and citrus fruits, cut through the mineral texture and promise a generous wine as it ages. Drink from 2020.','France','Burgundy','Chassagne-Montrachet',NULL,'Philippe Colin','Les Chenevottes Premier Cru'),(361,85,12,95,125.00,'Torbreck 2012 Descendant Shiraz-Viognier (Barossa Valley)','Bacon and tapenade elements merge easily on the nose, followed by a wine that\'s full bodied and creamy textured on the palate. This is dark and meaty in profile, yet not heavy or cooked, with a long, harmonious finish. Drink now–2030.','Australia','South Australia','Barossa Valley',NULL,'Torbreck','Descendant'),(362,48,1,95,60.00,'Bel Colle 2012 Simposio  (Barolo)','Enticing scents of ripe berry, underbrush, grilled herb and eucalyptus mingle together along with an underlying fragrance of rose petal. Elegant and fresh, the impeccably balanced palate delivers tart red cherry, cake spice, white pepper and mineral nuances alongside polished tannins. Drink 2018–2028.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Bel Colle','Simposio'),(363,9,7,95,200.00,'J. Davies 2012 Jamie Cabernet Sauvignon (Diamond Mountain District)','As impressive as the woman—a pioneer in the Napa Valley—was herself, this 100% varietal wine from the estate property high atop Diamond Mountain is powerfully elegant, intense yet refined. It begins with a high-toned, graceful entry that\'s rich in blueberry and chocolate, the oak smooth and integrated, with a suggestion of hand-rolled tobacco. Drink now through 2022.','US','California','Diamond Mountain District','Napa','J. Davies','Jamie'),(364,11,2,95,380.00,'Louis Latour 2014  Criots-Bâtard-Montrachet','This is an opulent wine from one of the fabled series of white Grand Crus. Along with generous yellow fruits and ripe citrus, it has weight and gravitas. Spice from the wood fills things out even more, giving the wine its balance, its intensity and its future. Drink from 2022.','France','Burgundy','Criots-Bâtard-Montrachet',NULL,'Louis Latour',NULL),(365,5,3,95,48.00,'Winderlea 2014 Weber Vineyard Pinot Noir (Dundee Hills)','For 2014, the Weber is the star of a very fine Winderlea lineup. Dark and deeply concentrated, it\'s jammed with black cherry fruit, annotated with anise and showing a hint of gunmetal. The tannins are ripe and taste of clean earth. This is a fine candidate for aging. Drink now through 2030.','US','Oregon','Dundee Hills','Willamette Valley','Winderlea','Weber Vineyard'),(366,67,12,95,60.00,'Wakefield 2013 St. Andrews Single Vineyard Release Shiraz (Clare Valley)','The Taylor family selected Clare Valley for its Cabernet affinity, but this Shiraz is a knockout. Yes, it\'s oaky—full of menthol, vanilla and toasted coconut—but there\'s just enough black cherry and plum fruit to support the wood. It\'s a plush, full-bodied wine with immense appeal, for drinking now–2025.','Australia','South Australia','Clare Valley',NULL,'Wakefield','St. Andrews Single Vineyard Release'),(367,65,12,88,21.00,'Cantina Terlano 2000 Vorberg Pinot Bianco (Alto Adige)','This spends 12 months in oak and it shows: It offers aromas of liquid smoke and flavors of brown sugar, honey and caramel. The fruit is subdued, leaving the emphasis on the oak and mineral components. Try with rich but delicately flavored fish dishes or mild chèvres.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'Cantina Terlano','Vorberg'),(368,36,5,88,10.00,'De Martino 1999 Reserva de la Familia Carmenère (Maipo Valley)','Aromas of mint, berry syrup and dense, lemony oak lay a good foundation for the heavy black fruit that comes on the palate atop a plush carpet of toasty, fresh-grained wood. The finish is round, tasty and mouthfilling, while overall the wine seems to dance due to popping acidity. This is Carmenère with a vital streak.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'De Martino','Reserva de la Familia'),(369,86,12,88,11.00,'Montresor 2001  Bianco di Custoza','A plump, juicy mouthful of citrusy fruit, worth trying with grilled or broiled seafood. The zesty lime aromas broaden out on the palate to include orange and tangerine flavors, making it tart but not too tart. Best Buy.','Italy','Veneto','Bianco di Custoza',NULL,'Montresor',NULL),(370,11,12,88,21.00,'Ronco del Gelso 1999 Chardonnay (Friuli)','This medium-weight wine flows effortlessly from start to finish, blending aromas of smoke and nuts with a citrusy core. Picks up savory nutty, cheesy notes (like a good Gruyère) on the long finish.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Friuli',NULL,'Ronco del Gelso',NULL),(371,9,9,88,160.00,'Sebastiani 1991 Cherryblock Vineyard Cabernet Sauvignon (Sonoma Valley)','Mint again, with earth and tobacco; one taster found traces of bell pepper. Coffee and brown sugar further soften a supple, mature mouthfeel. Drink now.','US','California','Sonoma Valley','Sonoma','Sebastiani','Cherryblock Vineyard'),(372,20,2,88,23.00,'Elena Walch 2002 Castel Ringberg Sauvignon Blanc (Alto Adige)','Fragrant, aromatic, grassy aromas give way to fresh, crisp, green fruit and gooseberry flavors. Finishes lively and vibrant.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'Elena Walch','Castel Ringberg'),(373,1,2,88,10.00,'Gini 2002 Classico  (Soave)','A fresh, crisp style of Soave, brimming with green plum and light acidity. It has concentration and a light touch in equal measure.','Italy','Veneto','Soave',NULL,'Gini','Classico'),(374,20,2,88,15.00,'Borgo Conventi 2002 I Fiori del Borgo Sauvignon Blanc (Collio)','Crisp, green, grassy wine with fresh acidity and herbeceous character. It is very New World with its tropical flavors and open, forward fruit.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Collio',NULL,'Borgo Conventi','I Fiori del Borgo'),(375,20,9,88,19.00,'Ceago Vinegarden 2001 Kathleen\'s Vineyard Sauvignon Blanc (Mendocino County)','An irresistibly drinkable white wine, filled with the juiciest flavors of citrus fruits, fig, melon and peach, and just the tiniest bit sweet. Crisp acidity cleanses the palate and leaves it feeling minty fresh on the long, spicy finish.','US','California','Mendocino County',NULL,'Ceago Vinegarden','Kathleen\'s Vineyard'),(376,29,9,88,40.00,'Valiano 1997 Vino in Musica Sangiovese (Toscana)','A soft, ripe wine that manages to showcase tobacco, earth and black cherry flavors in a relatively lightweight format, finishing long and tart.','Italy','Tuscany','Toscana',NULL,'Valiano','Vino in Musica'),(377,87,2,88,18.00,'Volpe Pasini 2002 Zuc de Volpe Pinot Grigio (Colli Orientali del Friuli)','A well-judged, well-structured wine that balances fresh, crisp and light fruit against flavors of peaches, almonds and cinnamon. It will be better in two or three years\' time.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Colli Orientali del Friuli',NULL,'Volpe Pasini','Zuc de Volpe'),(378,1,2,88,NULL,'Zenato 2001 Vigneto Massoni White (Naoussa)','A fresh, tangy, vibrant wine that has ripe green plum and apple flavors alongside a layer of full, forward fruit.','Greece','Naoussa',NULL,NULL,'Zenato','Vigneto Massoni'),(379,48,9,88,18.00,'L.A. Cetto 1996 Private Reserve Nebbiolo (Valle de Guadalupe)','The color is appropriately light, the aromas appropriately floral and rose-like. Fleshy cherry flavors are balanced by a helping of greens and flowers. Light and elegant. Who would\'ve thought Nebbiolo like this could come from Mexico?','Mexico','Valle de Guadalupe',NULL,NULL,'L.A. Cetto','Private Reserve'),(380,1,12,88,15.00,'La Vis 2001 Bianco dei Sorni White (Trentino)','This blend of Chardonnay, Nosiola and Pinot Bianco offers up apples and cream on the nose, along with flavors of peach and citrus. It\'s a comfortable mix of fruit that finishes lively and fresh, making it a fine apéritif.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Trentino',NULL,'La Vis','Bianco dei Sorni'),(381,16,5,88,12.00,'Lapostolle 2002 Estate Bottled Merlot (Rapel Valley)','At first this is aggressive, with an aromatic note of wet dog along with blueberries. But soon it finds its legs and opens to display chocolate, espresso and a big batch of black plum and blackberry. The finish has full tannins and some coffee-like flavor. Currently it\'s wall-to-wall big, but it should settle down in no time and become a good red to drink on any occasion.','Chile','Rapel Valley',NULL,NULL,'Lapostolle','Estate Bottled'),(382,1,12,88,11.00,'Fratelli Zeni 2000 Vigne Alte  (Bianco di Custoza)','It\'s testament to this wine\'s balance that it remains so alive and fresh long after many other Biancos have faded. Intensely mineral aromas mix with notes of smoke and fresh apples; the flavors are earthy and hint at mineral oil. Long on the finish. Best Buy.','Italy','Veneto','Bianco di Custoza',NULL,'Fratelli Zeni','Vigne Alte'),(383,9,5,88,15.00,'Carmen 2000 Estate Grown Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon (Maipo Valley)','With its herbal, traditional aromas, this New World Cabernet could impersonate and Old World model. The palate is tight and firm, with lively tannins and bracing acids. The flavors run toward plum and chocolate, and there\'s a bitter hint on the back palate. The finish is plummy and dark.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'Carmen','Estate Grown Reserve'),(384,11,12,88,9.00,'Tommasi 2001 Vigneto Santa Cecilia Chardonnay (Valdadige)','This lovely Chardonnay has just the right blend of juicy peaches and subtle herbs and flowers to make it easy to drink, yet interesting enough to hold your attention. Finishes long and mouthwatering.','Italy','Veneto','Valdadige',NULL,'Tommasi','Vigneto Santa Cecilia'),(385,8,2,88,30.00,'San Michele Eppan 2002 Sanct Valentin Gewürztraminer (Alto Adige)','Aromas of roses, pepper and spices make this an enticing wine. On the palate, it is ripe, soft, full-bodied and rich, lacking acidity, but otherwise classic Gewürztraminer.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'San Michele Eppan','Sanct Valentin'),(386,20,9,88,18.00,'Vinoce 2001 Sauvignon Blanc (Rutherford)','Richly textured, viscous but with good acidty for balance. The wine shows pretty melon, citrus, herb, grass, peach and spice flavors and features a mineral edge that is fresh and clean at the end.','US','California','Rutherford','Napa','Vinoce',NULL),(387,16,9,88,34.00,'Merriam 2000 Windacre Vineyard Merlot (Russian River Valley)','A first-rate wine, with well-ripened flavors of blackberries, espresso, cola, tea, and bitter chocolate, but made more interesting by fresh acidity not often seen in today\'s better Merlots. This cool-climate wine also has sturdy tannins that suggest mid-term aging.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Merriam','Windacre Vineyard'),(388,20,9,88,17.00,'Murphy-Goode 2000 Reserve Fume Sauvignon Blanc (Alexander Valley)','A great and versatile food wine. Its polished flavors of lime, fig and apricot are drizzled with Oriental spices and smoky oak. One of California\'s  most consistent wines, and rich enough to stand in for Chardonnay.','US','California','Alexander Valley','Sonoma','Murphy-Goode','Reserve Fume'),(389,5,2,88,25.00,'Kynsi 1999 Paragon Vineyard Pinot Noir (Edna Valley)','Delicate and complex, a cool climate wine with a mixture of ripe cherry flavors and leaner ones of tobacco, tomato skin, and cranberry. Bone dry with excellent acidity, this somewhat tart wine is well made, and may be an ager.','US','California','Edna Valley','Central Coast','Kynsi','Paragon Vineyard'),(390,1,12,88,15.00,'Cantina Terlano 2002 Terlano Classico White (Alto Adige)','A blend of grapes, so maybe it is not surprising that the aromas and flavors are a blend: melons, pears and limes, all presented with great freshness and verve alongside a rich texture. Editors\' Choice.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Alto Adige',NULL,'Cantina Terlano','Terlano Classico'),(391,9,5,88,12.00,'Casa Julia 2001 Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon (Maipo Valley)','Right off the bat this wine is pure and smooth. The nose is pretty, with cranberry and cassis. Next up is a palate of pure red fruit and only a light shading of oak. The finish draws applause for its clarity and buttery nuances. It\'s what a good Chilean Cabernet should be; it\'s ripe and easy to drink, yet fairly solid and impressive. Best Buy.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'Casa Julia','Reserve'),(392,11,5,88,14.00,'Valdivieso 2001 Reserve Chardonnay (Central Valley)','With full oak and pineapple aromas along with a big mouthful of spicy apple and pear fruit, this is no weakling. On the contrary, it\'s full and meaty, with a lot of texture and extract. The feel is healthy even if the acidity is on the low side. A very good wine to drink now; it probably won\'t age that well.','Chile','Central Valley',NULL,NULL,'Valdivieso','Reserve'),(393,20,9,87,12.00,'Bridlewood 2000 Sauvignon Blanc (Santa Ynez Valley)','A lovely wine, made even more attractive by the value price. It has flavors and lemons and limes and a ripe, sweet edge of honey, although it\'s technically dry. The acidity is clean and refreshing.','US','California','Santa Ynez Valley','Central Coast','Bridlewood',NULL),(394,11,5,87,11.00,'San Pedro 2002 Castillo de Molina Reserva Chardonnay (Lontué Valley)','Strongly oaked, but fresh, young and healthy in the nose. The smell of coconut and lemon curd is friendly and soft, while the palate is loaded with more lemon, coconut, pear and nutmeg. The texture is rich, and, for now, the acidity is bright. A solid Chardonnay for current drinking.','Chile','Lontué Valley',NULL,NULL,'San Pedro','Castillo de Molina Reserva'),(395,16,5,87,12.00,'Undurraga 2001 Reserva Merlot (Maipo Valley)','Smooth smelling, with pure and fresh berry and plum aromas. Very young and a bit tangy on the palate, with cherry and berry flavors and an oaky, soft finish that goes sweet then sour, and lasts for a long time. In terms of structure, it\'s balanced, mildly tannic, yet meant for drinking now.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'Undurraga','Reserva'),(396,1,2,87,NULL,'Conti Formentini 2001 Rylint White (Collio)','This is the first vintage of this blend of Chardonnay, Pinot Grigio and Sauvignon Blanc, named after the 16th-century abbess Rylint Formentini. Peppery in character, with rich, complex fruit, it has citric flavors, along with a sense of structure and acidity.','Italy','Northeastern Italy','Collio',NULL,'Conti Formentini','Rylint'),(397,40,9,85,16.00,'Cline 2007 Ancient Vines Zinfandel (California)','Rich in spicy, briary berry-cherry and chocolate fruit, with ultra-smooth tannins, and just enough acidity to cut through barbecue sauce. It\'s a bit sweet and Porty on its own.','US','California','California','California Other','Cline','Ancient Vines'),(398,5,5,85,15.00,'Cono Sur 2008 Visión Pinot Noir (Colchagua Valley)','Fresh aromas of red cherry and light berry fruit precede a palate that runs a little racy, with borderline tart plum and pie cherry flavors. A solid mouthfeel and mild, chalky tannins give it presence, and for sure it\'s a clean, sturdy wine. But that\'s really as far as it goes.','Chile','Colchagua Valley',NULL,NULL,'Cono Sur','Visión'),(399,20,5,85,13.00,'Aresti 2008 Estate Selection Sauvignon Blanc (Curicó Valley)','On the plump but balanced side, with a perfumed nose that\'s almost sweet for SB. In the mouth, it\'s fairly lively and lifted, with nectarine and melon flavors that morph into pink grapefruit on the finish. Decent quality; will get the job done.','Chile','Curicó Valley',NULL,NULL,'Aresti','Estate Selection'),(400,80,9,85,24.00,'Astoria 2008 Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','The wine starts off slowly due to a note of almond nut or cardboard that masks the natural fruit. Once it gets started, however, this luminous sparkling Prosecco offers cheerful notes of stone fruit and pear.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Astoria','Extra Dry'),(401,80,9,85,13.00,'Cantine Maschio NV Brut Prosecco (Italy)','Tonic and lean with a nearly transparent color and lively perlage, this non-DOC Prosecco offers candy-like aromas of butterscotch and lemon soda. There\'s an interesting touch of crushed white peppercorn in there as well and this well-priced wine would make a perfect match to appetizers and finger foods.','Italy','Italy Other','Italy',NULL,'Cantine Maschio','Brut'),(402,80,9,85,19.00,'Val d\'Oca 2008 Millesimato Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','This Extra Dry (slightly sweet) vintage Prosecco delivers a lean, slightly watery style and piquant bubbles that recall lemon soda. The wine is firm and steely in the mouth with tonic bubbling and layers of fresh fruit on the close.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Val d\'Oca','Millesimato Extra Dry'),(403,47,5,85,11.00,'Viña Bisquertt 2007 Casa la Joya Reserve Syrah (Colchagua Valley)','Formerly doing business as “Shiraz,” this Syrah from Bisquertt offers a huge purple tint, roasted aromas of blackberry and campfire, and a ripe, grapey palate that brims with simple, racy black cherry, pepper and other driving flavors. Not timid by any means but also nothing out of the ordinary.','Chile','Colchagua Valley',NULL,NULL,'Viña Bisquertt','Casa la Joya Reserve'),(404,15,9,85,15.00,'Vinavanti 2005 Le Bon Viveur Red (California)','Dry and acidic, this light-bodied wine has tart flavors of mashed cherries, cherryskins, orange zest and citrus fruits. It\'s a Bordeaux blend with Zinfandel and Sangiovese. Nice with pizza with prosciutto and olives.','US','California','California','California Other','Vinavanti','Le Bon Viveur'),(405,47,9,85,45.00,'Vino V 2005 White Hawk Vineyard Syrah (Santa Barbara County)','Smells funky, with sweaty leather aromas, although you\'ll also find varietal notes of the grape. Tastes all right, with blackberries, currants, leather and mocha that are wrapped into firm tannins.','US','California','Santa Barbara County','Central Coast','Vino V','White Hawk Vineyard'),(406,80,9,85,19.00,'Viticoltori Ponte NV Extra Dry  (Prosecco del Veneto)','Citrus tones, peach, white flower and mineral notes come forward thanks to the wine\'s bright personality and zesty effervescence. There are soft notes of crushed pepper and loads of sweet stone fruit flavors to enjoy as well.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco del Veneto',NULL,'Viticoltori Ponte','Extra Dry'),(407,31,2,85,30.00,'Jacquart NV Brut Mosaïque  (Champagne)','A creamy, caramel- and pear-flavored wine, keeping freshness but enriched with an almond and custard tart finish.','France','Champagne','Champagne',NULL,'Jacquart','Brut Mosaïque'),(408,11,5,85,14.00,'Lapostolle 2007 Casa Chardonnay (Casablanca Valley)','Aromas of baked apple, nut oil and toast are mildly appealing, while the round, dry palate is home to flavors of melon and bitter pith. The finish of peach pit and citrus peel is par for the course, and overall it\'s time to get at this standard Chardonnay before it goes flaccid.','Chile','Casablanca Valley',NULL,NULL,'Lapostolle','Casa'),(409,80,9,85,15.00,'Le Vigne di Alice 2008 Millesimato Extra Dry  (Prosecco di Conegliano e Valdobbiadene)','This Prosecco delivers medium intensity and a compact, slightly watery mouthfeel followed by lime, kiwi, white flower, honey and chopped basil. The cheerful sparkler ends with creamy consistency thanks to the foamy quality of its effervescence.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Conegliano e Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Le Vigne di Alice','Millesimato Extra Dry'),(410,8,16,85,20.00,'McGregor 2007 Dry Gewürztraminer (Finger Lakes)','Fresh and delicate with floral and citrus overtones, this wine has an elegant character. Its dry, spicy flavors are subtle and refreshing, giving the wine food pairing flexibility. Ideally, though, think of spicy cuisine like Indian, Thai or Indonesian.','US','New York','Finger Lakes','Finger Lakes','McGregor','Dry'),(411,30,16,85,20.00,'Miles 2006 Cabernet Franc (Finger Lakes)','An elegant nose of violet and blackberry gives this Cab Franc a graceful start. On the palate, soft cherry and blackberry flavors are punctuated by spice and pepper. An interesting sip that will pair well with fowl, beef.','US','New York','Finger Lakes','Finger Lakes','Miles',NULL),(412,9,9,85,12.00,'Morro Bay 2006 Split Oak Vineyard Cabernet Sauvignon (California)','A nice Cabernet for this everyday price. Dry and smooth, it shows interesting flavors of black currants, plums, herbs and spice, with a touch of smoky oak.','US','California','California','California Other','Morro Bay','Split Oak Vineyard'),(413,80,9,85,20.00,'Perlage 2008 Canah Brut  (Prosecco di Valdobbiadene)','Canah Brut Prosecco exhibits a slightly more saturated golden color and intense notes of mature peach, dried apricot with delicate mineral tones in the background. This rich sparkler is fatter and denser than most Proseccos and boasts an attractively low price tag.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco di Valdobbiadene',NULL,'Perlage','Canah Brut'),(414,80,9,85,13.00,'Pizzolato 2007  Prosecco del Veneto','Here\'s an organically grown Prosecco with citrusy notes of lime and grapefruit backed by white mineral and orange blossom. The wine is firm and slightly sweet on the finish and offers an easy, no-fuss experience overall.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco del Veneto',NULL,'Pizzolato',NULL),(415,80,9,85,16.00,'Pizzolato NV Stefany Extra Dry  (Prosecco del Veneto)','Here\'s a Prosecco with a broad and far-reaching aspect to its aromatic profile that recalls roasted almonds, mature peach and yellow rose. There\'s a pungent note in there as well of ash or talc powder and the sparkler ends with a playful blast of piquant spice.','Italy','Veneto','Prosecco del Veneto',NULL,'Pizzolato','Stefany Extra Dry'),(416,4,16,85,14.00,'Red Newt Cellars 2007 Riesling (Finger Lakes)','Citrus and spice overtones dominate the nose of this elegant Riesling. On the palate, slightly sweet fruit flavors are balanced by mineral and spice. Pair with grilled seafood, salads and cheeses.','US','New York','Finger Lakes','Finger Lakes','Red Newt Cellars',NULL),(417,80,9,85,14.00,'Ca\'Tullio NV Extra Dry  (Prosecco del Veneto)','This is an easy-going Prosecco with lively tones of stone fruit 