nce)','Very fruity and fresh, this wine has crisp apples as well as red fruit giving it a bright, delicious feeling. The acidity goes right through the wine, giving a beautifully fresh feel that points up the fragrant raspberries. Vineyards are in the heart of the sandy soils of the Saint Tropez peninsula.','France','Provence','Côtes de Provence',NULL,'Domaine de la Bastide Blanche','TwoB'),(708,39,2,91,20.00,'Domaine du Grand Cros 2014 L\'Esprit de Provence Rosé (Côtes de Provence)','Rounded and soft, this rich rosé is fruity while also perfumed. The blending of Syrah in the mix gives the wine a sense of power and concentration, making it an adquate partner at the dinner table.','France','Provence','Côtes de Provence',NULL,'Domaine du Grand Cros','L\'Esprit de Provence'),(709,39,2,91,25.00,'Domaine Sainte-Marie 2014 VieVité Extraordinaire Rosé (Côtes de Provence)','This wine is full in the mouth with a taste between pepper and fruit. It\'s ripe, rounded and tangy with clementine zest as well crisp apples and red currants. It could benefit from a few months in bottle, so drink from late 2015.','France','Provence','Côtes de Provence',NULL,'Domaine Sainte-Marie','VieVité Extraordinaire'),(710,40,7,91,38.00,'Dry Creek Vineyard 2012 DCV2 Estate Four Clones Vineyard Zinfandel (Dry Creek Valley)','Only the second vintage of this vineyard-designate wine from an estate property, this bottling offers spicy cherry, black tea and dried herb, backed by oaky backbone and structure. Dark chocolate and leather play on the palate in subtle waves, hitting their strides on the finish. Cellar through 2020.','US','California','Dry Creek Valley','Sonoma','Dry Creek Vineyard','DCV2 Estate Four Clones Vineyard'),(711,5,12,91,120.00,'Dry River 2013 Pinot Noir (Martinborough)','As typical for Dry River Pinots, this one is pretty surly in its youth. Intense and astringent, it packs layers of dusty black-cherry fruit into a tightly coiled frame. Try after 2019.','New Zealand','Martinborough',NULL,NULL,'Dry River',NULL),(712,20,7,91,23.00,'Dutton Estate 2013 Cohen Vineyard Dutton Ranch Sauvignon Blanc (Russian River Valley)','Floral and herbal from the get-go, this medium-bodied white from a great vineyard offers a lot to like. Stainless-steel fermentation gives it a lean underbelly, rounded out by sharp Meyer lemon and tangerine, buoyed by mouthwatering acidity. Green apple and an accent of honey peak on the finish.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Dutton Estate','Cohen Vineyard Dutton Ranch'),(713,5,7,91,48.00,'Failla 2013 Keefer Ranch Pinot Noir (Russian River Valley)','Light in color and weight, this vineyard-designate conveys a wealth of rose petals, earth and bright, crisp red cherry. Compellingly layered and shy, it defines the term ethereal. The finish is medium in length and accented in spicy cardamom.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Failla','Keefer Ranch'),(714,5,7,91,32.00,'Friedeman 2013 Dichotomy Pinot Noir (Russian River Valley)','This wine combines fruit from both cool and warm sites, which in the vintage might have both leaned on the warmer side. Black fruit and licorice give it a burly character at first. Decanting or letting the wine open in the glass will help, but still it retains smooth, velvety tannins and resolved oak.','US','California','Russian River Valley','Sonoma','Friedeman','Dichotomy'),(715,5,12,91,50.00,'Akarua 2012 Bannockburn Pinot Noir (Central Otago)','Alluring notes of Asian five spice and wet stone frame ripe cherry aromas in this medium-bodied wine. The texture is firm, becoming faintly dusty on the finish, but the wine is approachable now for its cherry fruit and appealing damp clay quality. Drink now–2018.','New Zealand','Central Otago',NULL,NULL,'Akarua','Bannockburn'),(716,15,5,91,28.00,'Benvenuto de la Serna 2010 Trisagio Malbec-Petit Verdot-Tannat Red (Valle de Uco)','Sweet oak and vanilla aromas are front and center on a jammy bouquet that also features black plum and blackberry scents. This blend of Malbec, Petit Verdot and Tannat feels full, lifted and balanced. Ripe, enticing flavors of wild berry and cassis are backed by toast, chocolate, vanilla and coconut notes as well as heat and burn. Drink through 2019.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Valle de Uco',NULL,'Benvenuto de la Serna','Trisagio Malbec-Petit Verdot-Tannat'),(717,5,12,91,30.00,'Carrick 2013 Unravelled Pinot Noir (Central Otago)','Even Carrick\'s entry-level wine has turned out well in 2013, offering a sturdy, robust mouthful of dark fruit. Plum, espresso and dark chocolate mingle on the nose and palate, while the finish is long, faintly dusty and mouthwatering. Drink 2017–2025.','New Zealand','Central Otago',NULL,NULL,'Carrick','Unravelled'),(718,39,2,91,25.00,'JCB 2014 No. 5 Rosé (Côtes de Provence)','An addition to the worldwide JCB brand, produced by the Boisset family of Burgundy, this feels rich and sumptuous, full of ripe red fruits and juicy plums. It is also balanced and well structured. Drink this wine with food.','France','Provence','Côtes de Provence',NULL,'JCB','No. 5'),(719,54,2,85,8.00,'Casca Wines 2015 Bote Chardonnay-Fernão Pires-Vital White (Lisboa)','Heading nicely in the crisp and aromatic direction, this is a light and bright wine. It has a citrus flavor that is balanced by richer pear and plum fruits. The wine is ready to drink.','Portugal','Lisboa',NULL,NULL,'Casca Wines','Bote Chardonnay-Fernão Pires-Vital'),(720,11,2,85,15.00,'Cave de Viré 2015 Grande Réserve du Président  (Mâcon-Villages)','This soft wine has a gentle texture and smooth white fruits. It is fruity and lightly perfumed. With its crisp edge of acidity, is totally ready to drink.','France','Burgundy','Mâcon-Villages',NULL,'Cave de Viré','Grande Réserve du Président'),(721,39,2,85,22.00,'Cortes de Cima 2015 Rosé (Alentejano)','Onion skin orange in color, this is a full and fat wine. It has attractive red-berry fruit and just the right amount of acidity to keep it fresh and crisp. Drink now.','Portugal','Alentejano',NULL,NULL,'Cortes de Cima',NULL),(722,9,5,85,14.00,'Domaine Bousquet 2015 Cabernet Sauvignon (Tupungato)','Saucy berry and tea aromas are herbal, earthy and stewed. This feels full but syrupy. Flavors of cooked berry, molasses and mocha finish sweet and soupy, with only a touch of acidic offset.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Tupungato',NULL,'Domaine Bousquet',NULL),(723,110,5,85,25.00,'Mendel 2015 Semillon (Mendoza)','Mushy citrus and papaya aromas are waxy and lack pop. Angular and lemony in feel, this varietal white offers a one-note flavor profile based on lemon. A ringing, citric finish affords for a hint of tropical fruit.','Argentina','Mendoza Province','Mendoza',NULL,'Mendel',NULL),(724,54,2,85,8.00,'Messias 2015 Santola White (Vinho Verde)','In a medium sweet style, the wine has a light prickle and fine citrus acidity to balance the soft freshness. It is a refreshing wine, totally drinkable immediately.','Portugal','Vinho Verde',NULL,NULL,'Messias','Santola'),(725,44,4,85,14.00,'Mont Sec 2015 Mont Sec Vineyards Viognier (Texas)','Peach, banana peel and a slight petrol note show mildly on the nose. The round palate boasts tart peach, pineapple rind and bitter lemon zest.','US','Texas','Texas',NULL,'Mont Sec','Mont Sec Vineyards'),(726,48,1,85,80.00,'Paolo Manzone 2012 Meriame  (Barolo)','This has aromas that recall leafy underbrush, sawdust and menthol. The dense, oak-driven palate shows licorice, espresso, toast and a hint of bitter chocolate but the fruit has dried up. It abruptly ends on a green note of powdered sage.','Italy','Piedmont','Barolo',NULL,'Paolo Manzone','Meriame'),(727,39,2,85,9.00,'Quinta de Paços 2015 Casa de Paços Rosé (Vinho Verde)','A rose pink colored wine that is dry and with ripe fruit. Its acidity contrasts with the warm red-berry fruit and the edge of tannin. There is a peppery, crisp aftertaste.','Portugal','Vinho Verde',NULL,NULL,'Quinta de Paços','Casa de Paços'),(728,5,3,85,13.00,'Rascal