riffin'),(767,5,12,87,18.00,'42°S 2008 Pinot Noir (Tasmania)','Light, fresh and silky—just what might be expected from cool-climate Pinot Noir. A pleasant earthiness underscores prettily interwoven strands of herbs and cherries. It\'s exciting to see the burgeoning quality of the wines coming out of Tasmania.','Australia','Tasmania','Tasmania',NULL,'42°S',NULL),(768,88,5,87,9.00,'Manyana 2008 Tempranillo (Cariñena)','Aromas of red licorice candy and raspberry are fruity, forward and clean. The palate is more than competent and balanced, with creamy strawberry and raspberry flavors. The finish is short but easy, and for the price that\'s all you can ask for.','Spain','Northern Spain','Cariñena',NULL,'Manyana',NULL),(769,9,12,87,11.00,'McWilliam\'s Hanwood Estate 2008 Cabernet Sauvignon (South Eastern Australia)','A good value in easy-to-drink Cabernet, McWilliam\'s 2008 is plummy and chocolaty, with soft tannins and a velvety finish. A bit simple perhaps, but definitely satisfying. Drink now.','Australia','Australia Other','South Eastern Australia',NULL,'McWilliam\'s Hanwood Estate',NULL),(770,33,9,87,30.00,'Paternoster 2007 Synthesi  (Aglianico del Vulture)','Here\'s a jammy, overtly ripe expression of Aglianico that ultimately proves to be an easier and more immediate expression of this naturally tannic grape variety. Aromas include candied fruit, blackberry preserves, raw cherry and raisin.','Italy','Southern Italy','Aglianico del Vulture',NULL,'Paternoster','Synthesi'),(771,11,2,92,62.00,'G. H. Mumm NV Mumm de Cramant Blanc de Blancs Chardonnay (Champagne)','Now with its intensity and some bottle age, this wine—formerly known as Crémant de Cramant—is rich, with its apple flavor blending with an almond note and a soft, warm texture. The acidity shoots right through this ripe wine.','France','Champagne','Champagne',NULL,'G. H. Mumm','Mumm de Cramant Blanc de Blancs'),(772,82,9,92,40.00,'Iron Horse 2007 Ocean Reserve Sparkling (Green Valley)','A beautiful sparkling 