','Buttonwood',NULL),(796,32,2,90,35.00,'Château Corbin 2014 Divin de Corbin  (Saint-Émilion)','This is the second wine from one of the group of chateaus with Corbin in their names. It is a tight wine, firm with tannins and with a concentrated texture and flavors of over-extraction. That said, the wine will probably develop over time into something serious with a dark, dense aftertaste.','France','Bordeaux','Saint-Émilion',NULL,'Château Corbin','Divin de Corbin'),(797,32,2,90,45.00,'Château Haut-Logat 2014  Haut-Médoc','This is a perfumed wine, with mint flavors as well as blackberry fruits. There is still a dominant structure of tannins and the wood aging that will allow the wine to age well. The fruits give the wine weight while the aftertaste has great swathes of acidity. Drink from 2019.','France','Bordeaux','Haut-Médoc',NULL,'Château Haut-Logat',NULL),(798,32,2,90,20.00,'Château La Branne 2014  Médoc','Produced from 30-year-old vines, this 55% Cabernet Sauvignon wine is firm with tannins as well as black-currant fruit. It is balanced with the potential to become a fruity wine with a soft texture. The acidity will keep it crisp and on point. Drink from 2018.','France','Bordeaux','Médoc',NULL,'Château La Branne',NULL),(799,32,2,90,17.00,'Château Mayne Vieil 2014  Fronsac','With ripe Merlot dominating this fine, blackberry flavored wine, it is fruity and rich. The acidity gives a crisper edge to the wine while the tannins come from a dry core. It is a wine in progress, full of potential and likely to be ready to drink from 2018.','France','Bordeaux','Fronsac',NULL,'Château Mayne Vieil',NULL),(800,32,2,90,45.00,'Château Mille-Roses 2012  Margaux','This 23-acre-estate is situated in the south of the Margaux appellation, close to classed growth Château Giscours. While not classified, it still has the ability to produce a fine ripe wine that also has great structure. Acidity and firm tannins are very present along with concentrated blackberry fruits. Drink this fine wine from 2019.','France','Bordeaux','Margaux',NULL,'Château Mille-Roses',NULL),(801,9,8,90,20.00,'Chessman 2014 Cabernet Sauvignon (Santa Ynez Valley)','With black cherry, blueberry, milk chocolate and balsamic reduction offsetting the light dill herbaceousness, this wine offers surprising depth for the affordable price. The texture is soft, yet the tannins stand up to the black cherry, charcoal and black-pepper flavors.','US','California','Santa Ynez Valley','Central Coast','Chessman',NULL),(802,47,7,90,50.00,'Deerfield Ranch NV Tawny Estate Syrah (Sonoma Valley)','Made entirely from Syrah grown on its property across multiple vintages, and then cave-aged six years in American oak, this is a nice dessert wine, raisiny and brimming in Christmas spice. With plenty of body and acidity, it swims effortlessly and smoothly on the palate, a bite of decadence that will work well with rich cheeses.','US','California','Sonoma Valley','Sonoma','Deerfield Ranch','Tawny Estate'),(803,19,2,90,22.00,'Domaine Franck Besson 2014 Le Griottier  (Juliénas)','This is a firm wine, balancing some solid tannins with ripe red fruits. Still young, it is packed with fruitiness and with acidity that are centered around a firm core. Drink this stylish wine from 2018.','France','Beaujolais','Juliénas',NULL,'Domaine Franck Besson','Le Griottier'),(804,16,10,90,39.00,'Efeste 2013 Upright Klipsun Vineyard Merlot (Red Mountain)','Aromas of savory herbs, mineral, exotic spice and red fruit are followed by fruit flavors that are surprisingly restrained considering the warmth of the vintage. Tart acidity livens it up. It\'s green for the variety but still brings enjoyment.','US','Washington','Red Mountain','Columbia Valley','Efeste','Upright Klipsun Vineyard'),(805,11,10,90,35.00,'Efeste 2014 Lola Evergreen Vineyard Chardonnay (Ancient Lakes)','The aromas of mineral, spice, toast, yellow apple and lemon pith are light but enchanting. The palate is medium bodied and refined, demonstrating judicious use of oak and a lengthy finish that shows some warmth.','US','Washington','Ancient Lakes','Columbia Valley','Efeste','Lola Evergreen Vineyard'),(806,4,3,90,15.00,'Firesteed 2012 Riesling (Oregon)','Bone dry and replete with skin flavors of pear and grapefruit pith, this is perfect for those who want to keep their alcohol consumption down without turning to a sweeter style of wine. Try it with grilled sausages and sauerkraut.','US','Oregon','Oregon','Oregon Other','Firesteed',NULL),(807,11,11,90,27.00,'Iron Hub 2014 Small Lot Chardonnay (Sierra Foothills)','Very smooth, almost thick, this is a rich wine in flavor and mouthfeel. It practically oozes over the palate, dripping with ripe pineapple, vanilla and cream, and coats every corner of the mouth before lingering through a long finish. It\'s full bodied, soft and concentrated.','US','California','Sierra Foothills','Sierra Foothills','Iron Hub','Small Lot'),(808,11,12,90,66.00,'Kooyong 2013 Farrago Chardonnay (Mornington Peninsula)','Without any new oak or lees stirring, this wine\'s sole focus is on the fruit. Pineapple, melon and peach notes are pure and striking, supported by just hints of vanilla and cream. This medium-bodied Chardonnay finishes in a flurry of tangerine and lime.','Australia','Victoria','Mornington Peninsula',NULL,'Kooyong','Farrago'),(809,116,1,90,32.00,'Moncaro 2015 Le Vele  (Verdicchio dei Castelli di Jesi Classico)','Aromas of ripe orchard fruit and chopped herb jump out of the glass. The savory palate serves up juicy Bartlett pear, green apple, citrus and a mint note while a hint of white almond adds depth. Very appealing.','Italy','Central Italy','Verdicchio dei Castelli di Jesi Classico',NULL,'Moncaro','Le Vele'),(810,88,5,90,20.00,'Finca Constancia 2011 Parcela 23 Tempranillo (Vino de la Tierra de Castilla)','Mild raisin, black cherry, anise and burnt tire aromas lead to a plump, balanced palate that\'s full but not overloaded. Earthy baked black-fruit flavors show a hint of oaky coconut, 