lley)','Good introductory Carmenère. It\'s a touch green, which is common for this quality level, but there\'s also some coconut and mild burnt aromas to wade through. Lively and clanky on the palate, with red fruit, bramble and herbal snap. Good if you\'re not expecting too much.','Chile','Maipo Valley',NULL,NULL,'Morandé','Pionero'),(971,9,9,85,19.00,'One Hope 2006 Cabernet Sauvignon (California)','A little tough and gritty, but okay for everyday fare. Shows blackberry, currant, tobacco and herb flavors that turn sweetly fruity on the finish.','US','California','California','California Other','One Hope',NULL),(972,31,2,85,15.00,'Pommery NV Pop Rosé Extra Dry  (Champagne)','Although it is labeled “Extra Dry” (that is sweeter than Brut), this lively Champagne in its festive little pink bottle is very fresh, with delicious acidity. It finishes lightly, easily.','France','Champagne','Champagne',NULL,'Pommery','Pop Rosé Extra Dry'),(973,44,9,85,23.00,'Saddleback 2008 Viognier (Clarksburg)','Sweet in jammy apricots and pineapples, with even richer notes of smoky vanilla and buttered toast. Crisp acidity fortunately provides some balance. From Venge Vineyards.','US','California','Clarksburg','Central Valley','Saddleback',NULL),(974,47,9,85,35.00,'Alexander Valley Vineyards 2006 Alexander School Reserve Big Barrel Syrah (Alexander Valley)','A bit earthy and herbal, and soft, with cherry and cocoa fruit flavors. The acidity and tannin structure could be firmer.','US','California','Alexander Valley','Sonoma','Alexander Valley Vineyards','Alexander School Reserve Big Barrel'),(975,15,3,85,30.00,'Covington 2006 Rough House Red Red (Walla Walla Valley (WA))','It\'s soft, slightly oxidized, and generic. It\'s pleasantly quaffable, marked in the finish by some rather bitter toast.','US','Washington','Walla Walla Valley (WA)','Columbia Valley','Covington','Rough House Red'),(976,5,9,85,12.00,'Feudo Montoni 2008 P Pinot Noir (Sicilia)','Fabio Sireci is behind some of Sicily\'s bes